SELECT 
    T1.School, 
    T2.`Free Meal Count (Ages 5-17)` / T2.`Enrollment (Ages 5-17)` AS EligibleFreeRate5To17
FROM 
    schools AS T1
INNER JOIN 
    frpm AS T2
ON 
    T1.CDSCode = T2.CDSCode
WHERE 
    T1.EdOpsName = 'Continuation School'
ORDER BY 
    EligibleFreeRate5To17 ASC
LIMIT 3;

SELECT 
    (CAST(T1.`Free Meal Count (Ages 5-17)` AS REAL) / CAST(T1.`Enrollment (Ages 5-17)` AS REAL)) AS EligibleFreeRate
FROM 
    frpm AS T1
INNER JOIN 
    schools AS T2
ON 
    T1.CDSCode = T2.CDSCode
WHERE 
    T2.EILName = 'Continuation School'
ORDER BY 
    EligibleFreeRate ASC
LIMIT 3;

SELECT 
    `County Name`, 
    `School Name`, 
    (`Free Meal Count (Ages 5-17)` / `Enrollment (Ages 5-17)`) AS `Free Meal Eligible Rate (Ages 5-17)`
FROM 
    frpm
WHERE 
    `Educational Option Type` = 'Continuation School'
ORDER BY 
    `Free Meal Count (Ages 5-17)` / `Enrollment (Ages 5-17)`
LIMIT 3;

SELECT 
    f.`Free Meal Count (Ages 5-17)`, 
    f.`Enrollment (Ages 5-17)`, 
    (CAST(f.`Free Meal Count (Ages 5-17)` AS REAL) / f.`Enrollment (Ages 5-17)`) AS EligibleFreeRate
FROM 
    frpm AS f
INNER JOIN 
    schools AS s
ON 
    f.CDSCode = s.CDSCode
WHERE 
    s.EdOpsName = 'Continuation School'
ORDER BY 
    EligibleFreeRate ASC
LIMIT 3;

SELECT 
    CAST(`Free Meal Count (Ages 5-17)` AS REAL) / CAST(`Enrollment (Ages 5-17)` AS REAL) AS EligibleFreeRate
FROM 
    frpm
WHERE 
    `Educational Option Type` = 'Continuation School'
ORDER BY 
    EligibleFreeRate ASC
LIMIT 3;

SELECT 
    frpm.`Free Meal Count (Ages 5-17)` / frpm.`Enrollment (Ages 5-17)` AS EligibleFreeRate
FROM 
    frpm
INNER JOIN 
    schools
ON 
    frpm.CDSCode = schools.CDSCode
WHERE 
    schools.EdOpsName = 'Continuation School'
ORDER BY 
    EligibleFreeRate ASC
LIMIT 3;

SELECT 
    T2.`School Name`, 
    CAST(T2.`Free Meal Count (Ages 5-17)` AS REAL) / T2.`Enrollment (Ages 5-17)` AS EligibleFreeRate
FROM 
    schools AS T1
INNER JOIN 
    frpm AS T2
ON 
    T1.CDSCode = T2.CDSCode
WHERE 
    T1.Virtual = 'Y'
ORDER BY 
    EligibleFreeRate ASC
LIMIT 3;

SELECT 
    (T1.`Free Meal Count (Ages 5-17)` / T1.`Enrollment (Ages 5-17)`) AS Eligible_Free_Rate
FROM 
    frpm AS T1
INNER JOIN 
    schools AS T2
ON 
    T1.CDSCode = T2.CDSCode
WHERE 
    T1.`Educational Option Type` = 'Continuation School'
ORDER BY 
    Eligible_Free_Rate ASC
LIMIT 3;

SELECT MAX(T2.`Free Meal Count (Ages 5-17)` / T2.`Enrollment (Ages 5-17)`) AS MaxEligibleFreeRate
FROM satscores AS T1
INNER JOIN frpm AS T2 ON T1.cds = T2.CDSCode
WHERE T1.NumGE1500 / T1.NumTstTakr > 0.3;

SELECT MAX(CAST(T2.`Free Meal Count (Ages 5-17)` AS REAL) / T2.`Enrollment (Ages 5-17)`)
FROM satscores AS T1
INNER JOIN frpm AS T2 ON T1.cds = T2.CDSCode
WHERE CAST(T1.NumGE1500 AS REAL) / T1.NumTstTakr > 0.3;

SELECT MAX(f.`Free Meal Count (Ages 5-17)` * 1.0 / f.`Enrollment (Ages 5-17)`) AS MaxEligibleFreeRate
FROM satscores s
INNER JOIN schools sc ON s.cds = sc.CDSCode
INNER JOIN frpm f ON sc.CDSCode = f.CDSCode
WHERE s.NumGE1500 * 1.0 / s.NumTstTakr > 0.3;

SELECT MAX(f.`Free Meal Count (Ages 5-17)` * 1.0 / f.`Enrollment (Ages 5-17)`) AS MaxEligibleFreeRate
FROM satscores AS s
INNER JOIN frpm AS f ON s.cds = f.CDSCode
WHERE s.NumTstTakr > 0 -- Ensure no division by zero
  AND (s.NumGE1500 * 1.0 / s.NumTstTakr) > 0.3;

SELECT MAX(f.`Free Meal Count (Ages 5-17)` / f.`Enrollment (Ages 5-17)`) AS MaxEligibleFreeRate
FROM schools s
INNER JOIN satscores sat ON s.CDSCode = sat.cds
INNER JOIN frpm f ON s.CDSCode = f.CDSCode
WHERE sat.NumGE1500 / sat.NumTstTakr > 0.3;

SELECT MAX(f.`Free Meal Count (Ages 5-17)` * 1.0 / f.`Enrollment (Ages 5-17)`) AS MaxEligibleFreeRate
FROM satscores s
INNER JOIN frpm f ON s.cds = f.CDSCode
WHERE s.NumGE1500 * 1.0 / s.NumTstTakr > 0.3;

SELECT MAX((T2.`Free Meal Count (Ages 5-17)` * 1.0) / T2.`Enrollment (Ages 5-17)`) AS MaxEligibleFreeRate
FROM schools AS T1
INNER JOIN satscores AS T3 ON T1.CDSCode = T3.cds
INNER JOIN frpm AS T2 ON T1.CDSCode = T2.CDSCode
WHERE (T3.NumGE1500 * 1.0) / T3.NumTstTakr > 0.3;

SELECT MAX(f."Free Meal Count (Ages 5-17)" * 1.0 / f."Enrollment (Ages 5-17)") AS MaxEligibleFreeRate
FROM satscores AS s
INNER JOIN frpm AS f ON s.cds = f.CDSCode
WHERE s.NumGE1500 * 1.0 / s.NumTstTakr > 0.3;

WITH RankedSchools AS (
    SELECT 
        cds,
        CAST(NumGE1500 AS REAL) / NumTstTakr AS ExcellenceRate,
        ROW_NUMBER() OVER (ORDER BY CAST(NumGE1500 AS REAL) / NumTstTakr DESC) AS rank
    FROM satscores
)
SELECT s.Phone
FROM RankedSchools rs
INNER JOIN schools s ON rs.cds = s.CDSCode
WHERE rs.rank <= 3;

SELECT 
    COALESCE(AdmFName1, '') || ' ' || COALESCE(AdmLName1, '') AS Admin1,
    COALESCE(AdmFName2, '') || ' ' || COALESCE(AdmLName2, '') AS Admin2,
    COALESCE(AdmFName3, '') || ' ' || COALESCE(AdmLName3, '') AS Admin3
FROM 
    schools AS T1
INNER JOIN 
    satscores AS T2
ON 
    T1.CDSCode = T2.cds
ORDER BY 
    T2.NumGE1500 DESC
LIMIT 1;

SELECT 
    CASE 
        WHEN T2.NumGE1500 > 0 THEN 
            COALESCE(T1.AdmFName1 || ' ' || T1.AdmLName1, 
                     T1.AdmFName2 || ' ' || T1.AdmLName2, 
                     T1.AdmFName3 || ' ' || T1.AdmLName3)
        ELSE 'No Administrator Found'
    END AS Administrator
FROM 
    schools AS T1
INNER JOIN 
    satscores AS T2 
ON 
    T1.CDSCode = T2.cds
ORDER BY 
    T2.NumGE1500 DESC
LIMIT 1;

SELECT 
    CASE 
        WHEN AdmLName1 IS NOT NULL THEN AdmFName1 || ' ' || AdmLName1
        ELSE NULL 
    END AS Admin1,
    CASE 
        WHEN AdmLName2 IS NOT NULL THEN AdmFName2 || ' ' || AdmLName2
        ELSE NULL 
    END AS Admin2,
    CASE 
        WHEN AdmLName3 IS NOT NULL THEN AdmFName3 || ' ' || AdmLName3
        ELSE NULL 
    END AS Admin3
FROM satscores AS T1
INNER JOIN schools AS T2 ON T1.cds = T2.CDSCode
ORDER BY T1.NumGE1500 DESC
LIMIT 1;

SELECT 
    CASE 
        WHEN T1.AdmFName1 IS NOT NULL AND T1.AdmLName1 IS NOT NULL THEN T1.AdmFName1 || ' ' || T1.AdmLName1
        WHEN T1.AdmFName2 IS NOT NULL AND T1.AdmLName2 IS NOT NULL THEN T1.AdmFName2 || ' ' || T1.AdmLName2
        WHEN T1.AdmFName3 IS NOT NULL AND T1.AdmLName3 IS NOT NULL THEN T1.AdmFName3 || ' ' || T1.AdmLName3
        ELSE 'No Administrator Found'
    END AS Administrator
FROM schools AS T1
INNER JOIN satscores AS T2 ON T1.CDSCode = T2.cds
ORDER BY T2.NumGE1500 DESC
LIMIT 1;

SELECT 
    CASE 
        WHEN T1.AdmFName1 IS NOT NULL THEN T1.AdmFName1 || ' ' || T1.AdmLName1
        WHEN T1.AdmFName2 IS NOT NULL THEN T1.AdmFName2 || ' ' || T1.AdmLName2
        WHEN T1.AdmFName3 IS NOT NULL THEN T1.AdmFName3 || ' ' || T1.AdmLName3
    END AS AdministratorName
FROM schools AS T1
INNER JOIN satscores AS T2 ON T1.CDSCode = T2.cds
WHERE T2.NumGE1500 = (SELECT MAX(NumGE1500) FROM satscores);

SELECT

-- SQL query to find the county with the most closed schools and list the schools along with their closure dates
WITH ClosedSchoolsByCounty AS (
    SELECT County, COUNT(*) AS ClosedCount
    FROM schools
    WHERE StatusType = 'Closed'
    GROUP BY County
    ORDER BY ClosedCount DESC
    LIMIT 1
)
SELECT s.School, s.ClosedDate
FROM schools AS s
JOIN ClosedSchoolsByCounty AS c
ON s.County = c.County
WHERE s.StatusType = 'Closed';

FROM schools

-- SQL query to find the county with the most closed schools and list all schools in that county
WITH ClosedSchools AS (
    SELECT County, School, ClosedDate
    FROM schools
    WHERE StatusType = 'Closed'
),

    SELECT County, COUNT(*) AS ClosedCount
    FROM ClosedSchools
    GROUP BY County
    ORDER BY ClosedCount DESC
    LIMIT 1
)

FROM ClosedSchools cs
JOIN CountyClosedCounts ccc ON cs.County = ccc.County;

-- SQL query to find the county with the most closed schools and list the school names and closure dates
WITH ClosedSchools AS (
    SELECT County, COUNT(*) AS ClosedCount
    FROM schools
    WHERE StatusType = 'Closed'
    GROUP BY County
),
MaxClosedCounty AS (
    SELECT County
    FROM ClosedSchools
    ORDER BY ClosedCount DESC
    LIMIT 1
)
SELECT s.County, s.School, s.ClosedDate
FROM schools s
JOIN MaxClosedCounty m ON s.County = m.County
WHERE s.StatusType = 'Closed'
ORDER BY s.School;

-- SQL query to count the number of cities and schools meeting the criteria
WITH MagnetSchools AS (
    SELECT s.City, COUNT(s.CDSCode) AS SchoolCount
    FROM schools s
    INNER JOIN frpm f ON s.CDSCode = f.CDSCode
    WHERE s.Magnet = 1
      AND s.GSserved = 'K-8'
      AND f.`NSLP Provision Status` = 'Multiple Provision Types'
    GROUP BY s.City
)
SELECT (SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT City) FROM MagnetSchools) AS TotalCities,
       MagnetSchools.City,
       MagnetSchools.SchoolCount
FROM MagnetSchools;

SELECT Name, District
FROM (
    SELECT AdmFName1 AS Name, District FROM schools WHERE AdmFName1 IS NOT NULL
    UNION ALL
    SELECT AdmFName2 AS Name, District FROM schools WHERE AdmFName2 IS NOT NULL
    UNION ALL
    SELECT AdmFName3 AS Name, District FROM schools WHERE AdmFName3 IS NOT NULL
) AS CombinedNames
GROUP BY Name, District
ORDER BY COUNT(*) DESC
LIMIT 2;

SELECT 
    T1.FirstName AS AdministratorsFirstName,
    T2.District AS AdministratorsDistrict
FROM (
    SELECT AdmFName1 AS FirstName FROM schools WHERE AdmFName1 IS NOT NULL
    UNION ALL
    SELECT AdmFName2 FROM schools WHERE AdmFName2 IS NOT NULL
    UNION ALL
    SELECT AdmFName3 FROM schools WHERE AdmFName3 IS NOT NULL
) AS T1
INNER JOIN schools AS T2
ON T1.FirstName = T2.AdmFName1 OR T1.FirstName = T2.AdmFName2 OR T1.FirstName = T2.AdmFName3
GROUP BY T1.FirstName, T2.District
ORDER BY COUNT(T1.FirstName) DESC
LIMIT 2;

SELECT AdminFirstName, District
FROM (
    SELECT AdmFName1 AS AdminFirstName, District FROM schools
    UNION ALL
    SELECT AdmFName2, District FROM schools
    UNION ALL
    SELECT AdmFName3, District FROM schools
) AS AdminNames
GROUP BY AdminFirstName, District
ORDER BY COUNT(*) DESC
LIMIT 2;

FROM (

    FROM schools
    UNION ALL

    FROM schools
    UNION ALL
    SELECT AdmFName3 AS FirstName, District
    FROM schools
) AS T1

SELECT Name, District

    FROM schools
    UNION ALL
    SELECT AdmFName3 AS Name, District
    FROM schools

GROUP BY Name, District

LIMIT 2;

SELECT FirstName, District
FROM (
    SELECT FirstName, COUNT(*) AS NameCount, District
    FROM (
        SELECT AdmFName1 AS FirstName, District FROM schools WHERE AdmFName1 IS NOT NULL
        UNION ALL
        SELECT AdmFName2, District FROM schools WHERE AdmFName2 IS NOT NULL
        UNION ALL
        SELECT AdmFName3, District FROM schools WHERE AdmFName3 IS NOT NULL
    ) AS AdminNames
    GROUP BY FirstName, District
)
ORDER BY NameCount DESC
LIMIT 2;

SELECT T1.District, T1.Name
FROM (
    SELECT District, AdmFName1 AS Name
    FROM schools
    UNION ALL
    SELECT District, AdmFName2 AS Name
    FROM schools
    UNION ALL
    SELECT District, AdmFName3 AS Name
    FROM schools
) AS T1
GROUP BY T1.Name
ORDER BY COUNT(*) DESC
LIMIT 2;

-- SQL query to find the two most common first names among school administrators and their districts
WITH AllAdminNames AS (
    SELECT AdmFName1 AS AdminName, District
    FROM schools
    UNION ALL
    SELECT AdmFName2, District
    FROM schools
    UNION ALL
    SELECT AdmFName3, District
    FROM schools
)
SELECT AdminName, District, COUNT(*) AS NameCount
FROM AllAdminNames
GROUP BY AdminName, District
ORDER BY NameCount DESC
LIMIT 2;

-- SQL query to solve the problem
WITH FemaleClients AS (
    SELECT c.client_id, c.birth_date, d.A11
    FROM client c
    INNER JOIN district d ON c.district_id = d.district_id
    WHERE c.gender = 'F'
),
OldestFemale AS (
    SELECT client_id, birth_date, A11
    FROM FemaleClients
    ORDER BY birth_date ASC
    LIMIT 1
),
LowestSalaryDistrict AS (
    SELECT MIN(A11) AS min_A11
    FROM FemaleClients
),
GapCalculation AS (
    SELECT MAX(A11) - (SELECT min_A11 FROM LowestSalaryDistrict) AS salary_gap
    FROM FemaleClients
)
SELECT a.account_id
FROM account a
INNER JOIN client c ON a.district_id = c.district_id
WHERE c.client_id = (SELECT client_id FROM OldestFemale)
  AND c.district_id = (SELECT district_id FROM district WHERE A11 = (SELECT min_A11 FROM LowestSalaryDistrict))
UNION ALL
SELECT salary_gap
FROM GapCalculation;

-- Step 1: Find the lowest average salary (A11)
WITH MinSalary AS (
    SELECT MIN(A11) AS lowest_salary
    FROM district
),
-- Step 2: Find clients with the lowest average salary and filter for females
OldestFemaleClients AS (
    SELECT c.client_id, c.birth_date, d.A11, a.account_id
    FROM client c
    INNER JOIN district d ON c.district_id = d.district_id
    INNER JOIN account a ON c.client_id = a.district_id
    WHERE c.gender = 'F' AND d.A11 = (SELECT lowest_salary FROM MinSalary)
),
-- Step 3: Find the oldest female clients
OldestClients AS (
    SELECT account_id
    FROM OldestFemaleClients
    ORDER BY birth_date ASC
    LIMIT 1
),
-- Step 4: Calculate the gap between highest and lowest average salary
SalaryGap AS (
    SELECT MAX(A11) - MIN(A11) AS salary_gap
    FROM district
)
-- Step 5: Combine results
SELECT oc.account_id, sg.salary_gap
FROM OldestClients oc
CROSS JOIN SalaryGap sg;

-- SQL query to find the account numbers of the oldest female clients with the lowest average salary
WITH FemaleClients AS (
    SELECT c.client_id, c.birth_date, d.A11, a.account_id
    FROM client c
    INNER JOIN district d ON c.district_id = d.district_id
    INNER JOIN account a ON c.district_id = a.district_id
    WHERE c.gender = 'F'
),
OldestLowestSalary AS (
    SELECT account_id, A11
    FROM FemaleClients
    ORDER BY birth_date ASC, A11 ASC
    LIMIT 1
),
SalaryGap AS (
    SELECT MAX(A11) - MIN(A11) AS gap
    FROM district
)
SELECT OldestLowestSalary.account_id, SalaryGap.gap
FROM OldestLowestSalary, SalaryGap;

-- SQL query to find account numbers of the oldest female clients and calculate the salary gap
WITH OldestFemaleClient AS (
    SELECT c.district_id, d.A11 AS avg_salary
    FROM client c
    INNER JOIN district d ON c.district_id = d.district_id
    WHERE c.gender = 'F'
    ORDER BY c.birth_date ASC
    LIMIT 1
),
SalaryGap AS (
    SELECT MAX(A11) - MIN(A11) AS salary_gap
    FROM district
)
SELECT a.account_id, sg.salary_gap
FROM OldestFemaleClient ofc
INNER JOIN account a ON ofc.district_id = a.district_id
CROSS JOIN SalaryGap sg;

-- Final query
SELECT A.account_id, (SELECT MAX(D.A11) - MIN(D.A11) FROM district AS D) AS salary_gap
FROM account AS A
INNER JOIN district AS D ON A.district_id = D.district_id
INNER JOIN disp AS DP ON A.account_id = DP.account_id
INNER JOIN client AS C ON DP.client_id = C.client_id
WHERE C.gender = 'F'
ORDER BY C.birth_date ASC
LIMIT 1;

-- Combined query
WITH FemaleClients AS (
    SELECT c.client_id, c.gender, c.birth_date, d.A11, a.account_id
    FROM client c
    INNER JOIN district d ON c.district_id = d.district_id
    INNER JOIN account a ON c.district_id = a.district_id
    WHERE c.gender = 'F'
),
OldestFemaleClients AS (
    SELECT account_id, A11
    FROM FemaleClients
    WHERE birth_date = (SELECT MAX(birth_date) FROM FemaleClients)
)
SELECT account_id
FROM OldestFemaleClients
WHERE A11 = (SELECT MIN(A11) FROM OldestFemaleClients)
UNION ALL
SELECT MAX(A11) - MIN(A11) AS salary_gap
FROM district;

-- SQL query to find the account numbers of the oldest female clients with the lowest average salary
WITH OldestFemaleClients AS (
    SELECT c.client_id, c.birth_date, d.A11
    FROM client c
    INNER JOIN account a ON c.district_id = a.district_id
    INNER JOIN district d ON a.district_id = d.district_id
    WHERE c.gender = 'F'
    ORDER BY c.birth_date ASC
    LIMIT 1
),
MinSalary AS (
    SELECT MIN(A11) AS min_A11
    FROM district
),
MaxSalary AS (
    SELECT MAX(A11) AS max_A11
    FROM district
)
SELECT a.account_id,
       (SELECT max_A11 - min_A11 FROM MinSalary, MaxSalary) AS salary_gap
FROM client c
INNER JOIN account a ON c.district_id = a.district_id
INNER JOIN district d ON a.district_id = d.district_id
WHERE c.client_id IN (SELECT client_id FROM OldestFemaleClients)
  AND d.A11 = (SELECT min_A11 FROM MinSalary);

-- SQL query to find the account numbers of the oldest female clients with the lowest average salary
WITH FemaleClients AS (
    SELECT c.client_id, c.district_id, c.birth_date, d.A11
    FROM client c
    INNER JOIN district d ON c.district_id = d.district_id
    WHERE c.gender = 'F'
),
OldestFemaleClient AS (
    SELECT client_id, district_id, birth_date, A11
    FROM FemaleClients
    ORDER BY birth_date ASC
    LIMIT 1
),
SalaryGap AS (
    SELECT MAX(A11) - MIN(A11) AS gap
    FROM district
)
SELECT a.account_id, g.gap
FROM OldestFemaleClient ofc
INNER JOIN account a ON ofc.client_id = a.account_id
CROSS JOIN SalaryGap g
WHERE ofc.A11 = (SELECT MIN(A11) FROM district);

-- SQL query to find the first transaction amount for the client who applied the biggest loan
WITH BiggestLoanClient AS (
    SELECT client.client_id
    FROM loan
    INNER JOIN account ON loan.account_id = account.account_id
    INNER JOIN disp ON account.account_id = disp.account_id
    INNER JOIN client ON disp.client_id = client.client_id
    ORDER BY loan.amount DESC
    LIMIT 1
),
FirstTransaction AS (
    SELECT trans.amount
    FROM trans
    INNER JOIN account ON trans.account_id = account.account_id
    INNER JOIN disp ON account.account_id = disp.account_id
    INNER JOIN client ON disp.client_id = client.client_id
    WHERE client.client_id = (SELECT client_id FROM BiggestLoanClient)
    ORDER BY trans.date ASC
    LIMIT 1
)
SELECT amount FROM FirstTransaction;

-- SQL query to find the first transaction amount after the account was opened for the client with the biggest loan
SELECT T3.amount
FROM loan AS T1
INNER JOIN account AS T2 ON T1.account_id = T2.account_id
INNER JOIN disp AS T4 ON T2.account_id = T4.account_id
INNER JOIN trans AS T3 ON T4.client_id = T3.account_id
WHERE T1.amount = (SELECT MAX(amount) FROM loan)
  AND T3.date > T2.date
ORDER BY T3.date ASC
LIMIT 1;

SELECT 
    ((MAX(CASE WHEN trans.date = '1998-12-27' THEN trans.balance END) - 
      MAX(CASE WHEN trans.date = '1993-03-22' THEN trans.balance END)) * 100.0 / 
     MAX(CASE WHEN trans.date = '1998-12-27' THEN trans.balance END)) AS increase_rate
FROM trans
INNER JOIN account ON trans.account_id = account.account_id
INNER JOIN loan ON account.account_id = loan.account_id
INNER JOIN disp ON loan.account_id = disp.account_id
WHERE loan.status = 'A' AND loan.date = '1993-07-05';

SELECT 
    CAST(
        (MAX(CASE WHEN T3.date = '1993-03-22' THEN T3.balance ELSE NULL END) - 
         MAX(CASE WHEN T3.date = '1998-12-27' THEN T3.balance ELSE NULL END)) AS REAL
    ) * 100 / 
    MAX(CASE WHEN T3.date = '1998-12-27' THEN T3.balance ELSE NULL END) AS increase_rate
FROM 
    loan AS T1
INNER JOIN 
    account AS T2 ON T1.account_id = T2.account_id
INNER JOIN 
    trans AS T3 ON T2.account_id = T3.account_id
WHERE 
    T1.`date` = '1993-07-05' 
    AND T1.status = 'A';

SELECT 
    ((T1.balance - T2.balance) * 100.0 / T2.balance) AS increase_rate
FROM 
    (SELECT balance FROM trans WHERE date = '1993-03-22') AS T1
JOIN 
    (SELECT balance FROM trans WHERE date = '1998-12-27') AS T2
ON 
    T1.account_id = T2.account_id
WHERE 
    T2.account_id = (SELECT A.account_id
                     FROM loan AS A
                     WHERE A.date = '1993-07-05');

SELECT 
    ((T1.balance - T2.balance) * 100.0 / T2.balance) AS increase_rate
FROM 
    trans AS T1
INNER JOIN 
    loan AS L ON T1.account_id = L.account_id
INNER JOIN 
    trans AS T2 ON T1.account_id = T2.account_id
WHERE 
    L.`date` = '1993-07-05'
    AND T1.`date` = '1993-03-22'
    AND T2.`date` = '1998-12-27';

SELECT 
    ((t2.balance - t1.balance) * 100.0 / t1.balance) AS increase_rate
FROM 
    loan l
INNER JOIN disp d ON l.account_id = d.account_id
INNER JOIN trans t1 ON d.account_id = t1.account_id AND t1.date = '1993-03-22'
INNER JOIN trans t2 ON d.account_id = t2.account_id AND t2.date = '1998-12-27'
WHERE 
    l.status = 'A' AND l.date = '1993-07-05';

SELECT 
    ((MAX(CASE WHEN T3.date = '1998-12-27' THEN T3.balance END) - MAX(CASE WHEN T3.date = '1993-03-22' THEN T3.balance END)) * 100.0) / MAX(CASE WHEN T3.date = '1998-12-27' THEN T3.balance END) AS increase_rate
FROM 
    loan AS T1
INNER JOIN 
    account AS T2 ON T1.account_id = T2.account_id
INNER JOIN 
    trans AS T3 ON T2.account_id = T3.account_id
WHERE 
    T1.status = 'A' AND T1.date = '1993-07-05';

-- SQL query to calculate the increase rate of the account balance
SELECT 
    ((balance_A - balance_B) * 100.0 / balance_B) AS increase_rate
FROM (
    SELECT 
        MAX(CASE WHEN T1.date = '1993-03-22' THEN T1.balance END) AS balance_A,
        MAX(CASE WHEN T1.date = '1998-12-27' THEN T1.balance END) AS balance_B
    FROM trans AS T1
    INNER JOIN account AS T2 ON T1.account_id = T2.account_id
    INNER JOIN loan AS T3 ON T2.account_id = T3.account_id
    WHERE T3.status = 'A' AND T3.date = '1993-07-05'
) AS subquery;

-- Step 1: Identify the client whose loan was approved first on 1993-07-05
WITH approved_loan_client AS (
    SELECT c.client_id
    FROM client c
    INNER JOIN disp d ON c.client_id = d.client_id
    INNER JOIN account a ON d.account_id = a.account_id
    INNER JOIN loan l ON a.account_id = l.account_id
    WHERE l.status = 'A' AND l.date = '1993-07-05'
),

-- Step 2: Retrieve balances for the identified client on the specified dates
balances AS (
    SELECT t.balance
    FROM approved_loan_client alc
    INNER JOIN disp d ON alc.client_id = d.client_id
    INNER JOIN account a ON d.account_id = a.account_id
    INNER JOIN trans t ON a.account_id = t.account_id
    WHERE t.date IN ('1993-03-22', '1998-12-27')
)

-- Step 3: Calculate the increase rate
SELECT 
    ((MAX(CASE WHEN t.date = '1993-03-22' THEN t.balance END) - 
      MAX(CASE WHEN t.date = '1998-12-27' THEN t.balance END)) / 
     MAX(CASE WHEN t.date = '1998-12-27' THEN t.balance END)) * 100 AS increase_rate
FROM balances b
INNER JOIN trans t ON b.balance = t.balance;

SELECT 
    CASE 
        WHEN SUM(CASE WHEN SUBSTR(lo.date, 1, 4) = '1996' THEN lo.amount ELSE 0 END) <> 0
        THEN (SUM(CASE WHEN SUBSTR(lo.date, 1, 4) = '1997' THEN lo.amount ELSE 0 END) - 
              SUM(CASE WHEN SUBSTR(lo.date, 1, 4) = '1996' THEN lo.amount ELSE 0 END)) * 100.0 /
             SUM(CASE WHEN SUBSTR(lo.date, 1, 4) = '1996' THEN lo.amount ELSE 0 END)
        ELSE 0
    END AS growth_rate
FROM loan lo
INNER JOIN account a ON lo.account_id = a.account_id
INNER JOIN client c ON a.district_id = c.district_id
WHERE c.gender = 'M';

SELECT 
    CAST(
        (SUM(CASE WHEN SUBSTR(l.date, 1, 4) = '1997' THEN l.amount ELSE 0 END) - 
         SUM(CASE WHEN SUBSTR(l.date, 1, 4) = '1996' THEN l.amount ELSE 0 END)
        ) AS REAL
    ) * 100.0 / 
    SUM(CASE WHEN SUBSTR(l.date, 1, 4) = '1996' THEN l.amount ELSE 0 END) AS growth_rate
FROM client c
INNER JOIN disp d ON c.client_id = d.client_id
INNER JOIN loan l ON d.account_id = l.account_id
WHERE c.gender = 'M';

SELECT 
    CAST(
        (SUM(CASE WHEN strftime('%Y', loan.date) = '1997' THEN loan.amount ELSE 0 END) - 
         SUM(CASE WHEN strftime('%Y', loan.date) = '1996' THEN loan.amount ELSE 0 END)) AS REAL
    ) * 100.0 / 
    SUM(CASE WHEN strftime('%Y', loan.date) = '1996' THEN loan.amount ELSE 0 END) AS growth_rate
FROM 
    client
INNER JOIN disp ON client.client_id = disp.client_id
INNER JOIN loan ON disp.account_id = loan.account_id
WHERE 
    client.gender = 'M';

SELECT 
    (CAST(SUM(CASE WHEN STRFTIME('%Y', loan.date) = '1997' THEN loan.amount ELSE 0 END) AS REAL) - 
     CAST(SUM(CASE WHEN STRFTIME('%Y', loan.date) = '1996' THEN loan.amount ELSE 0 END) AS REAL)) / 
    CAST(SUM(CASE WHEN STRFTIME('%Y', loan.date) = '1996' THEN loan.amount ELSE 0 END) AS REAL) * 100 AS growth_rate
FROM 
    loan
INNER JOIN 
    account ON loan.account_id = account.account_id
INNER JOIN 
    client ON account.district_id = client.district_id
WHERE 
    client.gender = 'M';

SELECT 
    CAST(
        (SUM(CASE WHEN strftime('%Y', loan.date) = '1997' THEN loan.amount ELSE 0 END) - 
         SUM(CASE WHEN strftime('%Y', loan.date) = '1996' THEN loan.amount ELSE 0 END)) 
        AS REAL
    ) * 100.0 / 
    SUM(CASE WHEN strftime('%Y', loan.date) = '1996' THEN loan.amount ELSE 0 END) AS growth_rate
FROM loan
INNER JOIN account ON loan.account_id = account.account_id
INNER JOIN client ON account.account_id = client.client_id
WHERE client.gender = 'M';

SELECT 
    (SUM(CASE WHEN STRFTIME('%Y', loan.date) = '1997' THEN loan.amount ELSE 0 END) - 
     SUM(CASE WHEN STRFTIME('%Y', loan.date) = '1996' THEN loan.amount ELSE 0 END)) * 100.0 /
    NULLIF(SUM(CASE WHEN STRFTIME('%Y', loan.date) = '1996' THEN loan.amount ELSE 0 END), 0) AS growth_rate
FROM 
    loan
INNER JOIN 
    account ON loan.account_id = account.account_id
INNER JOIN 
    client ON account.district_id = client.district_id
WHERE 
    client.gender = 'M';

SELECT 
    (SUM(CASE WHEN SUBSTR(l.date, 1, 4) = '1997' THEN l.amount ELSE 0 END) - 
     SUM(CASE WHEN SUBSTR(l.date, 1, 4) = '1996' THEN l.amount ELSE 0 END)) * 100.0 / 
     SUM(CASE WHEN SUBSTR(l.date, 1, 4) = '1996' THEN l.amount ELSE 0 END) AS growth_rate
FROM loan l
INNER JOIN account a ON l.account_id = a.account_id
INNER JOIN client c ON a.district_id = (SELECT district_id FROM client WHERE client_id = c.client_id)
WHERE c.gender = 'M';

    SUM(amount) AS total_amount
FROM trans AS T
INNER JOIN account AS A ON T.account_id = A.account_id
WHERE A.account_id = 3 AND T.k_symbol = 'statement release';

SELECT k_symbol, COUNT(*) AS frequency, SUM(amount) AS total_amount
FROM trans
WHERE account_id = 3 AND k_symbol = 'account statement'
GROUP BY k_symbol;

SELECT 
    SUM(CASE WHEN k_symbol = 'STOCK' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS num_stock_requests,
    k_symbol,
    SUM(amount) AS total_debit_amount
FROM 
    `order`
WHERE 
    account_to = 3
GROUP BY 
    k_symbol
HAVING 
    SUM(amount) = -3539;

-- Query for frequency of account statement requests (from the trans table)
SELECT 'Frequency' AS category, COUNT(*) AS value
FROM trans
WHERE account_id = 3 AND type = 'account_statement_request'

UNION ALL

-- Query for k_symbols with total debits of 3539 (from the order table)
SELECT 'k_symbol' AS category, k_symbol AS value
FROM order
GROUP BY k_symbol
HAVING SUM(amount) = 3539;

SELECT 
    SUM(CASE WHEN bank_to = 'ST' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS statement_requests,
    MAX(CASE WHEN amount = 3539 THEN k_symbol ELSE NULL END) AS purpose_of_debit
FROM `order`
WHERE account_id = 3;

SELECT 
    L.amount AS loan_amount,
    CASE 
        WHEN L.amount <= SUM(L.payments) THEN 'Paid in full'
        ELSE 'Partial or not paid'
    END AS payment_status
FROM 
    client C
INNER JOIN 
    disp D ON C.client_id = D.client_id
INNER JOIN 
    loan L ON D.account_id = L.account_id
WHERE 
    C.client_id = 992
GROUP BY 
    L.amount;

SELECT 
    L.amount AS loan_amount,
    CASE 
        WHEN L.payments = 0 THEN 'not paying'
        WHEN L.payments > 0 THEN 'paying'
        ELSE 'unknown'
    END AS payment_status
FROM 
    client C
INNER JOIN 
    disp D ON C.client_id = D.client_id
INNER JOIN 
    loan L ON D.account_id = L.account_id
WHERE 
    C.client_id = 992;

-- SQL query to find account numbers of the oldest female clients with the lowest average salary
WITH OldestClients AS (
    SELECT c.client_id, c.district_id, d.A11
    FROM client AS c
    INNER JOIN district AS d ON c.district_id = d.district_id
    WHERE c.gender = 'F'
    ORDER BY c.birth_date ASC
    LIMIT 1
)
SELECT a.account_id
FROM OldestClients AS oc
INNER JOIN account AS a ON oc.client_id = a.account_id
WHERE oc.A11 = (SELECT MIN(A11) FROM OldestClients);

SELECT a.account_id
FROM client c
INNER JOIN district d ON c.district_id = d.district_id
INNER JOIN account a ON c.client_id = a.account_id
WHERE c.gender = 'F'
  AND c.birth_date = (SELECT MIN(birth_date) FROM client WHERE gender = 'F')
  AND d.A11 = (SELECT MIN(A11) FROM district);

-- SQL query to find the account numbers of the oldest female clients with the lowest average salary
WITH OldestFemaleClients AS (
    SELECT c.client_id, c.district_id
    FROM client AS c
    WHERE c.gender = 'F'
      AND c.birth_date = (SELECT MIN(birth_date) FROM client WHERE gender = 'F')
),
LowestSalaryDistrict AS (
    SELECT d.district_id, MIN(d.A11) AS min_salary
    FROM district AS d
    INNER JOIN OldestFemaleClients AS ofc ON d.district_id = ofc.district_id
    GROUP BY d.district_id
),
Result AS (
    SELECT ofc.client_id, a.account_id
    FROM OldestFemaleClients AS ofc
    INNER JOIN account AS a ON ofc.district_id = a.district_id
    INNER JOIN district AS d ON ofc.district_id = d.district_id
    INNER JOIN LowestSalaryDistrict AS lsd ON d.district_id = lsd.district_id
    WHERE d.A11 = lsd.min_salary
)
SELECT account_id
FROM Result;

INNER JOIN district d ON c.district_id = d.district_id

  AND c.birth_date = (

    FROM client c2
    INNER JOIN district d2 ON c2.district_id = d2.district_id
    WHERE d2.A11 = (SELECT MIN(A11) FROM district)

SELECT a.account_id

INNER JOIN account a ON c.district_id = a.district_id

-- SQL query to calculate the average number of single-bonded atoms in carcinogenic molecules
WITH CarcinogenicMolecules AS (
    SELECT m.molecule_id
    FROM molecule m
    WHERE m.label = '+'
),
SingleBondedCounts AS (
    SELECT b.molecule_id, COUNT(b.bond_id) AS single_bonded_count
    FROM bond b
    JOIN CarcinogenicMolecules cm ON b.molecule_id = cm.molecule_id
    WHERE b.bond_type = '-'
    GROUP BY b.molecule_id
),
TotalAtomCounts AS (
    SELECT a.molecule_id, COUNT(a.atom_id) AS total_atom_count
    FROM atom a
    JOIN CarcinogenicMolecules cm ON a.molecule_id = cm.molecule_id
    GROUP BY a.molecule_id
)
SELECT SUM(sb.single_bonded_count) * 1.0 / SUM(ta.total_atom_count) AS average_single_bonded
FROM SingleBondedCounts sb
JOIN TotalAtomCounts ta ON sb.molecule_id = ta.molecule_id;

-- SQL query to calculate the percentage of carcinogenic molecules without fluorine
WITH fluorine_molecules AS (
    SELECT DISTINCT T1.molecule_id
    FROM molecule AS T1
    INNER JOIN atom AS T2 ON T1.molecule_id = T2.molecule_id
    WHERE T1.label = '+' AND T2.element = 'f'
),
all_carcinogenic_molecules AS (
    SELECT DISTINCT T1.molecule_id
    FROM molecule AS T1
    WHERE T1.label = '+'
)
SELECT CAST(
    (COUNT(DISTINCT all_carcinogenic_molecules.molecule_id) - COUNT(DISTINCT fluorine_molecules.molecule_id))
    AS REAL
) * 100.0 / COUNT(DISTINCT all_carcinogenic_molecules.molecule_id) AS percentage_without_fluorine
FROM all_carcinogenic_molecules
LEFT JOIN fluorine_molecules
ON all_carcinogenic_molecules.molecule_id = fluorine_molecules.molecule_id
WHERE fluorine_molecules.molecule_id IS NULL;

WITH CarcinogenicMolecules AS (
    SELECT T1.molecule_id
    FROM molecule AS T1
    INNER JOIN atom AS T2 ON T1.molecule_id = T2.molecule_id
    WHERE T1.label = '+'
    GROUP BY T1.molecule_id
    HAVING SUM(CASE WHEN T2.element = 'f' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) = 0
),
TotalCarcinogenicMolecules AS (
    SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT molecule_id) AS total_molecules
    FROM molecule
    WHERE label = '+'
),
MoleculesWithoutFluorine AS (
    SELECT COUNT(*) AS count_molecules_without_fluorine
    FROM CarcinogenicMolecules
)
SELECT CAST(MWOF.count_molecules_without_fluorine AS REAL) * 100.0 / TCM.total_molecules AS percentage
FROM MoleculesWithoutFluorine AS MWOF, TotalCarcinogenicMolecules AS TCM;

-- Step 1: Find the most common atom combination
WITH atom_combinations AS (
    SELECT T1.element AS element1, T2.element AS element2, COUNT(*) AS count
    FROM atom AS T1
    INNER JOIN connected AS C1 ON T1.atom_id = C1.atom_id
    INNER JOIN atom AS T2 ON C1.atom_id2 = T2.atom_id
    GROUP BY element1, element2
    ORDER BY count DESC
    LIMIT 1
),

-- Step 2: Count bonds for the most common combination
bonds_for_most_common AS (
    SELECT COUNT(*) AS bond_count
    FROM bond AS B
    INNER JOIN connected AS C1 ON B.bond_id = C1.bond_id
    INNER JOIN atom AS A1 ON C1.atom_id = A1.atom_id
    INNER JOIN atom AS A2 ON C1.atom_id2 = A2.atom_id
    WHERE (A1.element, A2.element) = (
        SELECT element1, element2 FROM atom_combinations
    )
),

-- Step 3: Calculate the percentage of bonds
total_bonds AS (
    SELECT COUNT(*) AS total_bond_count FROM bond
)
SELECT (CAST(bond_count AS REAL) / total_bond_count) * 100 AS percentage
FROM bonds_for_most_common, total_bonds;

-- SQL query to calculate the percentage of bonds with the most common combination of atoms' elements
WITH ElementPairs AS (
    SELECT 
        a1.element AS element1, 
        a2.element AS element2
    FROM connected AS c
    INNER JOIN atom AS a1 ON c.atom_id = a1.atom_id
    INNER JOIN atom AS a2 ON c.atom_id2 = a2.atom_id
),
ElementPairCounts AS (
    SELECT 
        element1, 
        element2, 
        COUNT(*) AS pair_count
    FROM ElementPairs
    GROUP BY element1, element2
),
MostCommonPair AS (
    SELECT element1, element2, pair_count
    FROM ElementPairCounts
    ORDER BY pair_count DESC
    LIMIT 1
),
BondsForMostCommonPair AS (
    SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT c.bond_id) AS bond_count
    FROM connected AS c
    INNER JOIN atom AS a1 ON c.atom_id = a1.atom_id
    INNER JOIN atom AS a2 ON c.atom_id2 = a2.atom_id
    INNER JOIN MostCommonPair AS mcp ON (a1.element = mcp.element1 AND a2.element = mcp.element2)
        OR (a1.element = mcp.element2 AND a2.element = mcp.element1)
)
SELECT 
    (CAST(bfmcp.bond_count AS REAL) / (SELECT COUNT(*) FROM atom)) * 100 AS percentage
FROM BondsForMostCommonPair AS bfmcp;

WITH element_counts AS (
    SELECT element, COUNT(*) AS atom_count
    FROM atom
    GROUP BY element
    ORDER BY atom_count DESC
    LIMIT 1
),
common_element_bonds AS (
    SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT T1.bond_id) AS bond_count
    FROM connected AS T1
    INNER JOIN atom AS T2 ON T1.atom_id = T2.atom_id
    INNER JOIN atom AS T3 ON T1.atom_id2 = T3.atom_id
    INNER JOIN element_counts AS EC ON T2.element = EC.element AND T3.element = EC.element
)
SELECT CAST(CB.bond_count AS REAL) * 100.0 / (SELECT COUNT(*) FROM bond) AS percentage
FROM common_element_bonds AS CB;

-- SQL query to calculate the percentage of bonds with the most common combination of atom elements
WITH atom_combinations AS (
    SELECT 
        A1.element AS element1, 
        A2.element AS element2, 
        COUNT(*) AS combination_count
    FROM 
        connected C
    INNER JOIN atom A1 ON C.atom_id = A1.atom_id
    INNER JOIN atom A2 ON C.atom_id2 = A2.atom_id
    GROUP BY A1.element, A2.element
),
most_common_combination AS (
    SELECT element1, element2
    FROM atom_combinations
    ORDER BY combination_count DESC
    LIMIT 1
)
SELECT 
    CAST(COUNT(B.bond_id) AS REAL) * 100.0 / (SELECT COUNT(*) FROM bond) AS percentage
FROM 
    bond B
INNER JOIN connected C ON B.bond_id = C.bond_id
INNER JOIN atom A1 ON C.atom_id = A1.atom_id
INNER JOIN atom A2 ON C.atom_id2 = A2.atom_id
CROSS JOIN most_common_combination MCC
WHERE 
    (A1.element = MCC.element1 AND A2.element = MCC.element2)
    OR (A1.element = MCC.element2 AND A2.element = MCC.element1);

-- SQL query to calculate the percentage of bonds with the most common combination of atoms' elements
WITH atom_combinations AS (
    -- Step 1: Get all combinations of atom elements connected by bonds
    SELECT a1.element AS element1, a2.element AS element2, b.bond_id
    FROM atom a1
    INNER JOIN connected c ON a1.atom_id = c.atom_id
    INNER JOIN atom a2 ON c.atom_id2 = a2.atom_id
    INNER JOIN bond b ON c.bond_id = b.bond_id
),
combination_counts AS (
    -- Step 2: Count occurrences of each element combination
    SELECT element1, element2, COUNT(*) AS combination_count
    FROM atom_combinations
    GROUP BY element1, element2
),
most_common_combination AS (
    -- Step 3: Find the most common combination
    SELECT element1, element2
    FROM combination_counts
    ORDER BY combination_count DESC
    LIMIT 1
),
total_bonds AS (
    -- Step 4: Count the total number of bonds
    SELECT COUNT(*) AS total_bond_count
    FROM bond
),
bonds_with_most_common AS (
    -- Step 5: Count bonds with the most common combination
    SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT ac.bond_id) AS count_bonds_with_most_common
    FROM atom_combinations ac
    INNER JOIN most_common_combination mcc
    ON ac.element1 = mcc.element1 AND ac.element2 = mcc.element2
)
-- Step 6: Calculate the percentage
SELECT 
    (bmc.count_bonds_with_most_common * 100.0) / tb.total_bond_count AS percentage
FROM bonds_with_most_common bmc, total_bonds tb;

-- SQL query to calculate the percentage of bonds with the most common combination of atoms' elements
WITH atom_combinations AS (
    SELECT 
        T1.bond_id,
        T2.element AS atom1_element,
        T3.element AS atom2_element
    FROM connected AS T1
    INNER JOIN atom AS T2 ON T1.atom_id = T2.atom_id
    INNER JOIN atom AS T3 ON T1.atom_id2 = T3.atom_id
),
element_combination_counts AS (
    SELECT 
        atom1_element,
        atom2_element,
        COUNT(bond_id) AS bond_count
    FROM atom_combinations
    GROUP BY atom1_element, atom2_element
),
most_common_combination AS (
    SELECT 
        atom1_element,
        atom2_element,
        bond_count
    FROM element_combination_counts
    ORDER BY bond_count DESC
    LIMIT 1
)
SELECT 
    (CAST(most_common_combination.bond_count AS REAL) / (SELECT COUNT(*) FROM bond)) * 100 AS percentage
FROM most_common_combination;

-- SQL query to calculate the percentage of bonds with the most common combination of atoms' elements
WITH element_combinations AS (
    SELECT 
        a1.element AS element1, 
        a2.element AS element2, 
        COUNT(c.bond_id) AS bond_count
    FROM connected AS c
    INNER JOIN atom AS a1 ON c.atom_id = a1.atom_id
    INNER JOIN atom AS a2 ON c.atom_id2 = a2.atom_id
    GROUP BY a1.element, a2.element
),
most_common_combination AS (
    SELECT element1, element2, bond_count
    FROM element_combinations
    WHERE bond_count = (SELECT MAX(bond_count) FROM element_combinations)
)
SELECT 
    CAST(most_common_combination.bond_count AS REAL) * 100 / (SELECT COUNT(*) FROM bond) AS percentage
FROM most_common_combination;

-- Step 1: Find the most common atom element
WITH atom_counts AS (
    SELECT element, COUNT(*) AS count
    FROM atom
    GROUP BY element
    ORDER BY count DESC
    LIMIT 1
),
-- Step 2: Count bonds for molecules with the most common element
bonds_with_most_common_element AS (
    SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT b.bond_id) AS bond_count
    FROM atom a
    INNER JOIN bond b ON a.molecule_id = b.molecule_id
    INNER JOIN atom_counts ac ON a.element = ac.element
)
-- Step 3: Calculate the percentage
SELECT 
    (CAST(bwme.bond_count AS REAL) * 100.0) / (SELECT COUNT(*) FROM bond) AS percentage
FROM bonds_with_most_common_element bwme;

    ELSE 'no'
END AS has_both_elements
FROM connected AS C
INNER JOIN atom AS A1 ON C.atom_id = A1.atom_id
INNER JOIN atom AS A2 ON C.atom_id2 = A2.atom_id
WHERE C.bond_id = 'TR001_1_8'
  AND A1.element IN ('cl', 'c')
  AND A2.element IN ('cl', 'c')
GROUP BY C.bond_id;

SELECT 
    CASE 
        WHEN SUM(CASE WHEN atom.element = 'cl' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) > 0
             AND SUM(CASE WHEN atom.element = 'c' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) > 0
        THEN 1
        ELSE 0
    END AS has_both_cl_and_c
FROM connected
INNER JOIN atom ON connected.atom_id = atom.atom_id
WHERE connected.bond_id = 'TR001_1_8';

SELECT 
    CASE 
        WHEN SUM(CASE WHEN A1.element = 'cl' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) > 0 
             AND SUM(CASE WHEN A1.element = 'c' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) > 0 
        THEN 1 
        ELSE 0 
    END AS has_both_cl_and_c
FROM 
    connected AS C1
LEFT JOIN 
    atom AS A1 ON C1.atom_id = A1.atom_id
WHERE 
    C1.bond_id = 'TR001_1_8';

SELECT DISTINCT
    CASE
        WHEN A1.element = 'cl' AND A2.element = 'c' THEN 1
        WHEN A1.element = 'c' AND A2.element = 'cl' THEN 1
        ELSE 0
    END AS has_cl_and_c
FROM connected AS C
INNER JOIN atom AS A1 ON C.atom_id = A1.atom_id
INNER JOIN atom AS A2 ON C.atom_id2 = A2.atom_id
WHERE C.bond_id = 'TR001_1_8';

SELECT 
    CASE 
        WHEN (A1.element = 'cl' AND A2.element = 'c') OR (A1.element = 'c' AND A2.element = 'cl') THEN 'yes'
        ELSE 'no'
    END AS result
FROM 
    connected AS C
INNER JOIN 
    atom AS A1 ON C.atom_id = A1.atom_id
INNER JOIN 
    atom AS A2 ON C.atom_id2 = A2.atom_id
WHERE 
    C.bond_id = 'TR001_1_8';

SELECT 
    CASE 
        WHEN SUM(CASE WHEN a.element = 'cl' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) > 0
             AND SUM(CASE WHEN a.element = 'c' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) > 0
        THEN 1
        ELSE 0
    END AS has_both_elements
FROM connected AS c
INNER JOIN atom AS a ON c.atom_id = a.atom_id
WHERE c.bond_id = 'TR001_1_8';

SELECT 
    CASE 
        WHEN SUM(CASE WHEN A1.element = 'cl' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) > 0 
             AND SUM(CASE WHEN A2.element = 'c' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) > 0 THEN 'yes'
        ELSE 'no'
    END AS has_cl_and_c
FROM connected AS C
INNER JOIN atom AS A1 ON C.atom_id = A1.atom_id
INNER JOIN atom AS A2 ON C.atom_id2 = A2.atom_id
WHERE C.bond_id = 'TR001_1_8';

         WHEN COUNT(DISTINCT A.element) = 2 AND 'cl' IN (A.element, B.element) AND 'c' IN (A.element, B.element) THEN 'yes'

INNER JOIN atom AS A ON C.atom_id = A.atom_id

-- SQL query to calculate the percentage of carcinogenic molecules with triple bonded hydrogen atoms
WITH triple_bonded_hydrogen AS (
    SELECT DISTINCT T1.molecule_id
    FROM atom AS T1
    INNER JOIN bond AS T2 ON T1.molecule_id = T2.molecule_id
    WHERE T1.element = 'h' AND T2.bond_type = '#'
),
carcinogenic_molecules AS (
    SELECT T3.molecule_id
    FROM triple_bonded_hydrogen AS T1
    INNER JOIN molecule AS T3 ON T1.molecule_id = T3.molecule_id
    WHERE T3.label = '+'
)
SELECT 
    CAST(COUNT(DISTINCT T2.molecule_id) AS REAL) * 100.0 / COUNT(DISTINCT T1.molecule_id) AS percentage
FROM triple_bonded_hydrogen AS T1
LEFT JOIN molecule AS T2 ON T1.molecule_id = T2.molecule_id;

    (SUM(CASE WHEN isTextless = 0 THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) * 100.0) / COUNT(*) AS percentage,
    id
FROM cards
WHERE isStorySpotlight = 1;

-- SQL query to calculate the percentage and list IDs
SELECT 
    (CAST(SUM(CASE WHEN isTextless = 0 THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS REAL) * 100.0 / COUNT(id)) AS percentage,
    id
FROM cards
WHERE isStorySpotlight = 1
GROUP BY id;

SELECT 
    CAST(SUM(CASE WHEN isTextless = 0 THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS REAL) * 100.0 / COUNT(*) AS percentage,
    id
FROM 
    cards
WHERE 
    isStorySpotlight = 1
GROUP BY 
    id;

SELECT 
    (CAST(SUM(CASE WHEN isTextless = 0 THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS REAL) * 100.0) / COUNT(*) AS percentage,
    id
FROM cards
WHERE isStorySpotlight = 1
GROUP BY id;

SELECT 
    id, 
    (COUNT(CASE WHEN isStorySpotlight = 1 AND isTextless = 1 THEN id END) * 100.0) / COUNT(id) AS percentage
FROM 
    cards
WHERE 
    isStorySpotlight = 1 AND isTextless = 1
GROUP BY 
    id;

-- Calculate the percentage and list card IDs
SELECT 
    CAST(SUM(CASE WHEN isTextless = 0 THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS REAL) * 100.0 / COUNT(*) AS percentage,
    id
FROM cards
WHERE isStorySpotlight = 1 AND isTextless = 0;

-- Calculate the percentage and list IDs
SELECT 
    CAST(SUM(CASE WHEN isStorySpotlight = 1 AND isTextless = 0 THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS REAL) * 100.0 / COUNT(*) AS percentage,
    GROUP_CONCAT(CASE WHEN isStorySpotlight = 1 AND isTextless = 0 THEN id ELSE NULL END) AS ids
FROM cards;

-- Combined query to show percentage and IDs
SELECT 
    (CAST(COUNT(CASE WHEN isTextless = 0 THEN id ELSE NULL END) AS REAL) * 100.0) / COUNT(id) AS percentage
FROM cards
WHERE isStorySpotlight = 1
UNION ALL
SELECT id
FROM cards
WHERE isStorySpotlight = 1 AND isTextless = 0;

SELECT 
    T2.name,
    CAST(SUM(CASE WHEN T1.language = 'Spanish' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS REAL) * 100.0 / COUNT(*) AS spanish_percentage
FROM 
    foreign_data AS T1
INNER JOIN 
    cards AS T2
ON 
    T1.uuid = T2.uuid
GROUP BY 
    T2.name
ORDER BY 
    T2.name;

SELECT 
    c.name,
    (COUNT(CASE WHEN f.language = 'Spanish' THEN 1 ELSE NULL END) * 100.0) / (SELECT COUNT(*) FROM cards) AS spanish_percentage
FROM 
    cards c
LEFT JOIN 
    foreign_data f
ON 
    c.uuid = f.uuid
GROUP BY 
    c.name
ORDER BY 
    c.name;

-- Calculate the percentage of Spanish cards and list their names
SELECT
    (CAST(SUM(CASE WHEN fd.language = 'Spanish' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS REAL) * 100) / COUNT(c.id) AS spanish_percentage,
    c.name
FROM
    cards c
LEFT JOIN
    foreign_data fd
ON
    c.uuid = fd.uuid
GROUP BY
    c.name
HAVING
    fd.language = 'Spanish' OR fd.language IS NULL;

SELECT 
    SUM(CASE WHEN fd.language = 'Spanish' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) * 100.0 / COUNT(c.id) AS spanish_percentage,
    c.name
FROM 
    cards AS c
LEFT JOIN 
    foreign_data AS fd
ON 
    c.uuid = fd.uuid
GROUP BY 
    c.name
ORDER BY 
    spanish_percentage DESC;

-- SQL query to calculate the percentage of cards in Spanish and list them by name
SELECT 
    CAST(SUM(CASE WHEN fd.language = 'Spanish' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS REAL) * 100.0 / COUNT(*) AS spanish_percentage,
    c.name
FROM 
    foreign_data AS fd
INNER JOIN 
    cards AS c
ON 
    fd.uuid = c.uuid
WHERE 
    fd.language = 'Spanish'
GROUP BY 
    c.name;

SELECT 
    c.name AS card_name,
    CAST(COUNT(CASE WHEN fd.language = 'Spanish' THEN 1 ELSE NULL END) AS REAL) * 100.0 / COUNT(c.id) AS spanish_percentage
FROM 
    cards AS c
INNER JOIN 
    foreign_data AS fd
ON 
    c.uuid = fd.uuid
GROUP BY 
    c.name;

-- SQL query to calculate the percentage of cards in Spanish and list their names
WITH spanish_cards AS (
    SELECT c.name
    FROM cards c
    INNER JOIN foreign_data fd ON c.uuid = fd.uuid
    WHERE fd.language = 'Spanish'
),
total_cards AS (
    SELECT COUNT(*) AS total_count
    FROM cards
),
spanish_count AS (
    SELECT COUNT(*) AS spanish_count
    FROM spanish_cards
)
SELECT 
    (sc.spanish_count * 100.0 / tc.total_count) AS percentage,
    scd.name AS card_name
FROM spanish_cards scd
CROSS JOIN spanish_count sc
CROSS JOIN total_cards tc;

SELECT 
    CAST(SUM(CASE WHEN T2.language = 'Spanish' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS REAL) * 100.0 / COUNT(T1.id) AS spanish_percentage,
    T1.name
FROM 
    cards AS T1
INNER JOIN 
    foreign_data AS T2
ON 
    T1.uuid = T2.uuid
GROUP BY 
    T1.name;

-- SQL query to find the format with the highest number of banned cards and list all banned card names
WITH banned_counts AS (
    SELECT L.format, COUNT(*) AS banned_count
    FROM legalities AS L
    INNER JOIN cards AS C ON L.uuid = C.uuid
    WHERE L.status = 'Banned'
    GROUP BY L.format
    ORDER BY banned_count DESC
    LIMIT 1
)
SELECT L.format, C.name
FROM legalities AS L
INNER JOIN cards AS C ON L.uuid = C.uuid
WHERE L.status = 'Banned' AND L.format = (SELECT format FROM banned_counts);

-- Step 1: Find the format with the highest number of banned cards
WITH banned_counts AS (
    SELECT format, COUNT(*) AS banned_count
    FROM legalities
    WHERE status = 'Banned'
    GROUP BY format
    ORDER BY banned_count DESC
    LIMIT 1
)

-- Step 2: Retrieve the card names for the format with the highest number of banned cards
SELECT L.format, C.name
FROM legalities AS L
INNER JOIN cards AS C ON L.uuid = C.uuid
WHERE L.status = 'Banned' AND L.format = (SELECT format FROM banned_counts);

-- Step 1: Find the format with the highest number of banned cards
WITH banned_counts AS (
    SELECT L.format, COUNT(*) AS banned_count
    FROM legalities AS L
    INNER JOIN cards AS C ON L.uuid = C.uuid
    WHERE L.status = 'Banned'
    GROUP BY L.format
    ORDER BY banned_count DESC
    LIMIT 1
)
-- Step 2: Retrieve the format and names of all cards banned in that format
SELECT bc.format, C.name
FROM banned_counts AS bc
INNER JOIN legalities AS L ON bc.format = L.format
INNER JOIN cards AS C ON L.uuid = C.uuid
WHERE L.status = 'Banned'
ORDER BY C.name;

-- SQL query to find the play format with the highest number of banned cards and list all banned card names
WITH banned_counts AS (
    SELECT format, COUNT(*) AS banned_count
    FROM legalities
    WHERE status = 'Banned'
    GROUP BY format
),
max_banned_format AS (
    SELECT format
    FROM banned_counts
    ORDER BY banned_count DESC
    LIMIT 1
)
SELECT l.format, c.name
FROM legalities l
INNER JOIN cards c ON l.uuid = c.uuid
WHERE l.status = 'Banned' AND l.format = (SELECT format FROM max_banned_format);

SELECT L.format, C.name
FROM legalities AS L
INNER JOIN cards AS C ON L.uuid = C.uuid
WHERE L.status = 'Banned'
ORDER BY L.format DESC, C.name ASC
LIMIT 1;

-- SQL query to find the format with the highest number of banned cards and their names
WITH banned_counts AS (
    SELECT L.format, COUNT(*) AS banned_count
    FROM legalities L
    WHERE L.status = 'Banned'
    GROUP BY L.format
    ORDER BY banned_count DESC
    LIMIT 1
)
SELECT L.format, C.name
FROM legalities L
INNER JOIN cards C ON L.uuid = C.uuid
WHERE L.status = 'Banned' AND L.format = (SELECT format FROM banned_counts);

-- SQL query to find the play format with the highest number of banned cards and list all banned card names
WITH banned_counts AS (
    SELECT T1.format, COUNT(*) AS banned_count
    FROM legalities AS T1
    INNER JOIN cards AS T2 ON T1.uuid = T2.uuid
    WHERE T1.status = 'Banned'
    GROUP BY T1.format
    ORDER BY banned_count DESC

SELECT T1.format, T2.name

INNER JOIN cards AS T2 ON T1.uuid = T2.uuid
WHERE T1.status = 'Banned' AND T1.format = (SELECT format FROM banned_counts);

    FROM cards AS T1
    INNER JOIN legalities AS T2 ON T1.uuid = T2.uuid
    WHERE T2.status = 'Banned'
    GROUP BY T2.format
    ORDER BY banned_count DESC

)

-- SQL query to find the illustrator with the least number of cards and list the formats of play for their cards
WITH artist_card_count AS (
    SELECT artist, COUNT(*) AS card_count
    FROM cards
    GROUP BY artist
    ORDER BY card_count ASC
    LIMIT 1
)
SELECT DISTINCT l.format
FROM legalities AS l
INNER JOIN cards AS c ON l.uuid = c.uuid
INNER JOIN artist_card_count AS acc ON c.artist = acc.artist;

-- SQL query to find the illustrator with the least number of cards and their formats
SELECT c.artist, l.format
FROM cards c
JOIN legalities l ON c.uuid = l.uuid
WHERE c.artist = (
    SELECT artist
    FROM cards
    GROUP BY artist
    ORDER BY COUNT(*) ASC
    LIMIT 1
);

-- Step 1: Find the artist with the least number of cards
WITH artist_counts AS (
    SELECT artist, COUNT(*) AS card_count
    FROM cards
    GROUP BY artist
),
min_count AS (
    SELECT MIN(card_count) AS min_card_count
    FROM artist_counts
)

-- Step 2: Retrieve the formats of play for the cards illustrated by the artist(s) with the minimum card count
SELECT c.artist, l.format
FROM cards c
JOIN legalities l ON c.uuid = l.uuid
JOIN artist_counts ac ON c.artist = ac.artist
JOIN min_count mc ON ac.card_count = mc.min_card_count
GROUP BY c.artist, l.format;

-- SQL query to calculate the annual average number of sets and the common language
WITH filtered_sets AS (
    SELECT s.code, s.releaseDate, f.language
    FROM sets s
    INNER JOIN foreign_data f ON s.code = f.multiverseid
    WHERE s.releaseDate BETWEEN '2012-01-01' AND '2015-12-31'
),
annual_counts AS (
    SELECT strftime('%Y', releaseDate) AS year, COUNT(code) AS set_count
    FROM filtered_sets
    GROUP BY strftime('%Y', releaseDate)
),
common_language AS (
    SELECT language
    FROM filtered_sets
    GROUP BY language
    ORDER BY COUNT(language) DESC
    LIMIT 1
)
SELECT AVG(set_count) AS annual_average, (SELECT language FROM common_language) AS common_language
FROM annual_counts;

-- Annual average number of sets and the most common language
WITH annual_set_counts AS (
    SELECT 
        STRFTIME('%Y', releaseDate) AS year, 
        COUNT(*) AS set_count
    FROM sets
    WHERE releaseDate BETWEEN '2012-01-01' AND '2015-12-31'
    GROUP BY STRFTIME('%Y', releaseDate)
),
language_counts AS (
    SELECT 
        STRFTIME('%Y', T1.releaseDate) AS year, 
        T2.language, 
        COUNT(T2.language) AS language_count
    FROM sets AS T1
    INNER JOIN foreign_data AS T2 
        ON T1.code = T2.multiverseid
    WHERE T1.releaseDate BETWEEN '2012-01-01' AND '2015-12-31'
    GROUP BY STRFTIME('%Y', T1.releaseDate), T2.language
)
SELECT 
    (SELECT AVG(set_count) FROM annual_set_counts) AS average_sets_per_year,
    (SELECT language FROM language_counts GROUP BY language ORDER BY SUM(language_count) DESC LIMIT 1) AS most_common_language;

-- SQL query to calculate the annual average number of sets released between 2012 and 2015
-- and find the most common language in the foreign_data table.
SELECT 
    CAST(COUNT(*) AS REAL) / 4 AS annual_average_sets
FROM sets
WHERE releaseDate BETWEEN '2012-01-01' AND '2015-12-31'
UNION ALL
SELECT 
    language AS most_common_language
FROM foreign_data
GROUP BY language
ORDER BY COUNT(*) DESC
LIMIT 1;

-- SQL query to calculate the annual average number of sets and the common language
WITH SetCounts AS (
    SELECT 
        strftime('%Y', releaseDate) AS year,
        COUNT(*) AS setCount
    FROM sets
    WHERE releaseDate BETWEEN '2012-01-01' AND '2015-12-31'
    GROUP BY year
),
LanguageCounts AS (
    SELECT 
        language,
        COUNT(*) AS languageCount
    FROM foreign_data
    GROUP BY language
),
CommonLanguage AS (
    SELECT language
    FROM LanguageCounts
    ORDER BY languageCount DESC
    LIMIT 1
)
SELECT 
    AVG(setCount) AS avgSetsPerYear,
    (SELECT language FROM CommonLanguage) AS commonLanguage
FROM SetCounts;

-- SQL query to calculate the annual average number of sets and the common language
WITH yearly_set_counts AS (
    SELECT
        SUBSTR(s.releaseDate, 1, 4) AS year,
        COUNT(s.code) AS num_sets
    FROM sets s
    WHERE s.releaseDate BETWEEN '2012-01-01' AND '2015-12-31'
    GROUP BY SUBSTR(s.releaseDate, 1, 4)
),
total_avg_yearly_sets AS (
    SELECT AVG(num_sets) AS avg_num_sets
    FROM yearly_set_counts
),
language_counts AS (
    SELECT st.language, COUNT(s.code) AS num_sets
    FROM sets s
    INNER JOIN set_translations st ON s.code = st.setCode
    WHERE s.releaseDate BETWEEN '2012-01-01' AND '2015-12-31'
    GROUP BY st.language
)
SELECT
    (SELECT avg_num_sets FROM total_avg_yearly_sets) AS avg_sets_per_year,
    (SELECT language FROM language_counts ORDER BY num_sets DESC LIMIT 1) AS common_language

-- Calculate the annual average number of sets released between 1/1/2012 and 12/31/2015
-- and determine the most common language of the cards.
SELECT 
    AVG(yearly_set_count) AS annual_average_sets,
    most_common_language
FROM (
    -- Subquery to calculate the yearly count of sets
    SELECT STRFTIME('%Y', releaseDate) AS year, COUNT(*) AS yearly_set_count
    FROM sets
    WHERE releaseDate BETWEEN '2012-01-01' AND '2015-12-31'
    GROUP BY STRFTIME('%Y', releaseDate)
) AS yearly_sets,
(
    -- Subquery to find the most common language
    SELECT language AS most_common_language
    FROM foreign_data
    GROUP BY language
    ORDER BY COUNT(language) DESC
    LIMIT 1
) AS language_info;

-- SQL query to calculate the annual average number of sets and the common language
WITH yearly_set_counts AS (
    SELECT 
        STRFTIME('%Y', releaseDate) AS year,
        COUNT(*) AS set_count
    FROM sets
    WHERE releaseDate BETWEEN '2012-01-01' AND '2015-12-31'
    GROUP BY STRFTIME('%Y', releaseDate)
),
common_language AS (
    SELECT 
        T3.language
    FROM sets AS T1
    INNER JOIN cards AS T2 ON T1.code = T2.setCode
    INNER JOIN foreign_data AS T3 ON T2.uuid = T3.uuid
    WHERE T1.releaseDate BETWEEN '2012-01-01' AND '2015-12-31'
    GROUP BY T3.language
    ORDER BY COUNT(T3.language) DESC
    LIMIT 1
)
SELECT 
    AVG(set_count) AS annual_average_sets,
    (SELECT language FROM common_language) AS most_common_language
FROM yearly_set_counts;

-- SQL query to calculate the annual average number of sets and the common language
SELECT 
    CAST(COUNT(DISTINCT T1.code) AS REAL) / 4 AS annual_average_sets,
    (SELECT T2.language
     FROM foreign_data AS T2
     GROUP BY T2.language
     ORDER BY COUNT(T2.language) DESC
     LIMIT 1) AS common_language
FROM sets AS T1
WHERE T1.releaseDate BETWEEN '2012-01-01' AND '2015-12-31';

       SUM(CASE WHEN T1.Numerator = 'Votes' THEN T2.Count ELSE 0 END) AS Ratio
FROM (
    SELECT 'Posts' AS Numerator, COUNT(*) AS Count
    FROM posts
    WHERE OwnerUserId = 24
    UNION ALL
    SELECT 'Votes' AS Numerator, COUNT(*) AS Count
    FROM votes
    WHERE UserId = 24
) AS T2;

WITH TagSplitCTE AS (
    SELECT
        p.Tags,
        1 AS TagIndex,
        1 AS StartIndex
    FROM posts p
    INNER JOIN users u ON p.OwnerUserId = u.Id
    WHERE u.DisplayName = 'John Salvatier'
    UNION ALL
    SELECT
        Tags,
        TagIndex + 1 AS TagIndex,
        INSTR(SUBSTR(Tags, StartIndex), '>') + StartIndex + 1 AS StartIndex
    FROM TagSplitCTE
    WHERE StartIndex < LENGTH(Tags)
)
SELECT DISTINCT
    SUBSTR(Tags, StartIndex, INSTR(SUBSTR(Tags, StartIndex), '>') - StartIndex) AS TagName
FROM TagSplitCTE
WHERE StartIndex > 1;

FROM users

INNER JOIN tags ON posts.Id = tags.ExcerptPostId OR posts.Id = tags.WikiPostId

SELECT MAX(TotalViewCount) AS HigherPopularity
FROM (
    SELECT OwnerDisplayName, SUM(ViewCount) AS TotalViewCount
    FROM posts
    WHERE OwnerDisplayName IN ('Harvey Motulsky', 'Noah Snyder')
    GROUP BY OwnerDisplayName
) AS UserViewCounts;

SELECT 
    CASE 
        WHEN SUM(CASE WHEN u.DisplayName = 'Harvey Motulsky' THEN p.ViewCount ELSE 0 END) 
             > SUM(CASE WHEN u.DisplayName = 'Noah Snyder' THEN p.ViewCount ELSE 0 END) 
        THEN 'Harvey Motulsky' 
        ELSE 'Noah Snyder' 
    END AS HigherPopularityUser
FROM users u
INNER JOIN posts p ON u.Id = p.OwnerUserId
WHERE u.DisplayName IN ('Harvey Motulsky', 'Noah Snyder');

-- Step 1: Find the maximum age in the Users table
WITH MaxAge AS (
    SELECT MAX(Age) AS MaxAge
    FROM users
),

-- Step 2: Identify the oldest users (those with the maximum age)
OldestUsers AS (
    SELECT Id
    FROM users
    WHERE Age = (SELECT MaxAge FROM MaxAge)
),

-- Step 3: Count the number of distinct posts voted by each oldest user
VotedPostsCount AS (
    SELECT V.UserId, COUNT(DISTINCT V.PostId) AS VotedPostCount
    FROM votes V
    INNER JOIN OldestUsers O ON V.UserId = O.Id
    GROUP BY V.UserId
)

-- Step 4: Calculate the average number of posts voted by the oldest users
SELECT AVG(VotedPostCount) AS AverageVotedPosts
FROM VotedPostsCount;

880:
SELECT 
    CAST(
        (T1.fastestLapSpeed - T2.fastestLapSpeed) AS REAL
    ) * 100 / T1.fastestLapSpeed AS percentage_difference
FROM 
    results AS T1
JOIN 
    results AS T2
ON 
    T1.driverId = T2.driverId
JOIN 
    drivers AS D
ON 
    T1.driverId = D.driverId
WHERE 
    T1.raceId = 853 
    AND T2.raceId = 854 
    AND D.forename = 'Paul' 
    AND D.surname = 'di Resta';

SELECT 
    CAST(
        (MAX(CASE WHEN T2.raceId = 853 THEN T2.fastestLapSpeed END) - 
         MAX(CASE WHEN T2.raceId = 854 THEN T2.fastestLapSpeed END)) AS REAL
    ) * 100.0 / MAX(CASE WHEN T2.raceId = 853 THEN T2.fastestLapSpeed END) AS percentage_difference
FROM 
    drivers AS T1
INNER JOIN 
    results AS T2
ON 
    T1.driverId = T2.driverId
WHERE 
    T1.forename = 'Paul' AND T1.surname = 'di Resta';

SELECT 
    (CAST(T2.fastestLapSpeed AS REAL) - CAST(T1.fastestLapSpeed AS REAL)) / CAST(T2.fastestLapSpeed AS REAL) * 100 AS percentage_difference
FROM 
    results AS T1
INNER JOIN 
    results AS T2 ON T1.driverId = T2.driverId
INNER JOIN 
    drivers ON T1.driverId = drivers.driverId
WHERE

SELECT COUNT(*) AS wins
FROM circuits AS T1
INNER JOIN races AS T2 ON T1.circuitId = T2.circuitId
INNER JOIN results AS T3 ON T2.raceId = T3.raceId
INNER JOIN drivers AS T4 ON T3.driverId = T4.driverId
WHERE T1.name = 'Sepang International Circuit'
  AND T4.forename = 'Michael'
  AND T4.surname = 'Schumacher';

SELECT COUNT(*)
FROM circuits AS c
INNER JOIN races AS r ON c.circuitId = r.circuitId
INNER JOIN results AS res ON r.raceId = res.raceId
INNER JOIN drivers AS d ON res.driverId = d.driverId
WHERE c.name = 'Sepang International Circuit'
  AND d.forename = 'Michael'
  AND d.surname = 'Schumacher'
  AND res.points = (
      SELECT MAX(points)
      FROM results AS res2
      WHERE res2.raceId = res.raceId
  );

FROM results AS r
INNER JOIN drivers AS d ON r.driverId = d.driverId
INNER JOIN races AS ra ON r.raceId = ra.raceId
INNER JOIN circuits AS c ON ra.circuitId = c.circuitId
WHERE d.forename = 'Michael'
  AND d.surname = 'Schumacher'
  AND c.name = 'Sepang International Circuit'
  AND r.points > 0;

SELECT AVG(
    CAST(SUBSTR(T2.fastestLapTime, 1, INSTR(T2.fastestLapTime, ':') - 1) AS INTEGER) * 60 +
    CAST(SUBSTR(T2.fastestLapTime, INSTR(T2.fastestLapTime, ':') + 1, INSTR(T2.fastestLapTime, '.') - INSTR(T2.fastestLapTime, ':') - 1) AS INTEGER) +
    CAST(SUBSTR(T2.fastestLapTime, INSTR(T2.fastestLapTime, '.') + 1) AS REAL) / 1000
) AS average_fastest_lap_time
FROM drivers AS T1
INNER JOIN results AS T2 ON T1.driverId = T2.driverId
WHERE T1.forename = 'Lewis' AND T1.surname = 'Hamilton';

SELECT AVG(
    CAST(SUBSTR(T2.fastestLapTime, 1, 2) AS INTEGER) * 60 + 
    CAST(SUBSTR(T2.fastestLapTime, 4, 2) AS INTEGER) + 
    CAST(SUBSTR(T2.fastestLapTime, 7, 3) AS REAL) / 1000.0
) AS average_fastest_lap_time
FROM drivers AS T1
INNER JOIN results AS T2 ON T1.driverId = T2.driverId
WHERE T1.forename = 'Lewis' AND T1.surname = 'Hamilton';

    CAST(SUBSTR(T2.fastestLapTime, 1, INSTR(T2.fastestLapTime, ':') - 1) AS REAL) * 60 +
    CAST(SUBSTR(T2.fastestLapTime, INSTR(T2.fastestLapTime, ':') + 1, 2) AS REAL) +
    CAST(SUBSTR(T2.fastestLapTime, INSTR(T2.fastestLapTime, '.') - 2) AS REAL) / 1000
) AS average_fastest_lap_time_seconds
FROM drivers AS T1

-- SQL query to calculate how much faster the champion is compared to the last driver
SELECT 
    100 * (
        (CAST(SUBSTR(champion_time, 1, 2) AS INTEGER) * 3600000 +
         CAST(SUBSTR(champion_time, 4, 2) AS INTEGER) * 60000 +
         CAST(SUBSTR(champion_time, 7, 2) AS INTEGER) * 1000 +
         CAST(SUBSTR(champion_time, 10, 3) AS INTEGER)) -
        (CAST(SUBSTR(last_driver_time, 1, 2) AS INTEGER) * 3600000 +
         CAST(SUBSTR(last_driver_time, 4, 2) AS INTEGER) * 60000 +
         CAST(SUBSTR(last_driver_time, 7, 2) AS INTEGER) * 1000 +
         CAST(SUBSTR(last_driver_time, 10, 3) AS INTEGER))
    ) / 
    (CAST(SUBSTR(last_driver_time, 1, 2) AS INTEGER) * 3600000 +
     CAST(SUBSTR(last_driver_time, 4, 2) AS INTEGER) * 60000 +
     CAST(SUBSTR(last_driver_time, 7, 2) AS INTEGER) * 1000 +
     CAST(SUBSTR(last_driver_time, 10, 3) AS INTEGER)) AS percentage_faster
FROM (
    SELECT 
        MAX(CASE WHEN position = 1 THEN time END) AS champion_time,
        MAX(time) AS last_driver_time
    FROM results
    INNER JOIN races ON results.raceId = races.raceId
    WHERE races.name = 'Australian Grand Prix' AND races.year = 2008
) subquery;

SELECT 
    (CAST(MAX(CASE WHEN R.position = 1 THEN R.milliseconds END) AS REAL) - 
     CAST(MAX(CASE WHEN R.position = (SELECT MAX(position) FROM results WHERE raceId = R.raceId) THEN R.milliseconds END) AS REAL)) /
    CAST(MAX(CASE WHEN R.position = (SELECT MAX(position) FROM results WHERE raceId = R.raceId) THEN R.milliseconds END) AS REAL) * 100 AS percentage_faster
FROM results R
INNER JOIN races RA ON R.raceId = RA.raceId
WHERE RA.year = 2008 AND RA.name = 'Australian Grand Prix';

WITH race_info AS (
    SELECT r.raceId, r.name, r.year
    FROM races r
    WHERE r.name = 'Australian Grand Prix' AND r.year = 2008
),
champion_time AS (
    SELECT res.time AS champion_time
    FROM results res
    INNER JOIN race_info ri ON res.raceId = ri.raceId
    ORDER BY res.time ASC
    LIMIT 1
),
incremental_time AS (
    SELECT SUM(strftime('%s', res.time) - strftime('%s', '00:00:00')) AS incremental_time
    FROM results res
    INNER JOIN race_info ri ON res.raceId = ri.raceId
),
calculated_times AS (
    SELECT ct.champion_time, it.incremental_time
    FROM champion_time ct, incremental_time it
)
SELECT 
    ((ct.incremental_time - ct.champion_time) / (ct.incremental_time + ct.champion_time)) * 100 AS percentage_faster
FROM calculated_times ct;

WITH Champion AS (
    SELECT MIN(time) AS champion_time
    FROM results
    WHERE raceId = (
        SELECT raceId
        FROM races
        WHERE name = 'Australian Grand Prix' AND year = 2008
    )
),
IncrementalTimes AS (
    SELECT
        LAG(TIME, 1) OVER (ORDER BY TIME) AS prev_time,
        TIME AS incremental_time
    FROM results
    WHERE raceId = (
        SELECT raceId
        FROM races
        WHERE name = 'Australian Grand Prix' AND year = 2008
    )
),
LastDriverTime AS (
    SELECT
        (SELECT champion_time FROM Champion) + (SELECT incremental_time FROM IncrementalTimes ORDER BY incremental_time DESC LIMIT 1) AS last_driver_time
)
SELECT
    ((SELECT champion_time FROM Champion) - (SELECT last_driver_time FROM LastDriverTime)) / (SELECT last_driver_time FROM LastDriverTime) * 100 AS how_much_faster

-- SQL query to calculate how much faster the champion is compared to the last driver
WITH race_times AS (
    SELECT T2.time AS champion_time
    FROM races AS T1
    INNER JOIN results AS T2 ON T1.raceId = T2.raceId
    WHERE T1.year = 2008 AND T1.name = 'Australian Grand Prix' AND T2.position = 1
    UNION ALL
    SELECT T2.time AS last_driver_time
    FROM races AS T1
    INNER JOIN results AS T2 ON T1.raceId = T2.raceId
    WHERE T1.year = 2008 AND T1.name = 'Australian Grand Prix'
    ORDER BY CAST(SUBSTR(T2.time, 1, 2) AS INTEGER) * 3600 + 
             CAST(SUBSTR(T2.time, 4, 2) AS INTEGER) * 60 + 
             CAST(SUBSTR(T2.time, 7, 2) AS INTEGER) + 
             CAST(SUBSTR(T2.time, 10, 3) AS REAL) / 1000
    LIMIT 1
)
SELECT 
    ((CAST(SUBSTR(champion_time, 1, 2) AS INTEGER) * 3600 + 
      CAST(SUBSTR(champion_time, 4, 2) AS INTEGER) * 60 + 
      CAST(SUBSTR(champion_time, 7, 2) AS INTEGER) + 
      CAST(SUBSTR(champion_time, 10, 3) AS REAL) / 1000) -
     (CAST(SUBSTR(last_driver_time, 1, 2) AS INTEGER) * 3600 + 
      CAST(SUBSTR(last_driver_time, 4, 2) AS INTEGER) * 60 + 
      CAST(SUBSTR(last_driver_time, 7, 2) AS INTEGER) + 
      CAST(SUBSTR(last_driver_time, 10, 3) AS REAL) / 1000)) /
    (CAST(SUBSTR(last_driver_time, 1, 2) AS INTEGER) * 3600 + 
     CAST(SUBSTR(last_driver_time, 4, 2) AS INTEGER) * 60 + 
     CAST(SUBSTR(last_driver_time, 7, 2) AS INTEGER) + 
     CAST(SUBSTR(last_driver_time, 10, 3) AS REAL) / 1000) * 100 AS how_much_faster
FROM race_times;

WITH champion AS (
    SELECT CAST(SUBSTR(T2.time, 1, 2) AS INTEGER) * 3600000 +
           CAST(SUBSTR(T2.time, 4, 2) AS INTEGER) * 60000 +
           CAST(SUBSTR(T2.time, 7, 2) AS INTEGER) * 1000 +
           CAST(SUBSTR(T2.time, 10, 3) AS INTEGER) AS champion_time_ms
    FROM races AS T1
    INNER JOIN results AS T2 ON T1.raceId = T2.raceId
    WHERE T1.year = 2008 AND T1.name = 'Australian Grand Prix' AND T2.position = 1
),
last_driver AS (
    SELECT SUM(T2.milliseconds) + T1.champion_time_ms AS last_driver_time_ms
    FROM races AS T1
    INNER JOIN results AS T2 ON T1.raceId = T2.raceId
    CROSS JOIN champion
    WHERE T1.year = 2008 AND T1.name = 'Australian Grand Prix'
    AND T2.position > 1
    AND T2.time IS NOT NULL
)
SELECT (T1.champion_time_ms - T2.last_driver_time_ms) * 100.0 / T2.last_driver_time_ms AS how_much_faster
FROM champion AS T1, last_driver AS T2;

-- SQL Query to calculate how much faster the champion is compared to the last driver
WITH IncrementalTimes AS (
    SELECT 
        l1.raceId,
        l1.driverId,
        l1.lap,
        l1.milliseconds - COALESCE((SELECT l2.milliseconds 
                                     FROM laptimes l2 
                                     WHERE l2.raceId = l1.raceId AND l2.driverId = l1.driverId AND l2.lap = l1.lap - 1), 0) AS incremental_time
    FROM laptimes l1
),
ChampionTime AS (
    SELECT r.time AS champion_time
    FROM results r
    INNER JOIN races ra ON r.raceId = ra.raceId
    WHERE ra.year = 2008 AND ra.name = 'Australian Grand Prix' AND r.position = 1
),
LastDriverTime AS (
    SELECT SUM(it.incremental_time) + CAST(REPLACE(ct.champion_time, ':', '.') AS REAL) AS last_driver_time
    FROM IncrementalTimes it
    CROSS JOIN ChampionTime ct
    INNER JOIN races ra ON it.raceId = ra.raceId
    WHERE ra.year = 2008 AND ra.name = 'Australian Grand Prix'
    AND it.lap = (SELECT MAX(lap) FROM laptimes WHERE raceId = it.raceId)
)
SELECT 
    ((CAST(REPLACE(ct.champion_time, ':', '.') AS REAL) - ldt.last_driver_time) / ldt.last_driver_time) * 100 AS percent_faster
FROM ChampionTime ct, LastDriverTime ldt;

-- SQL query to calculate how much faster the champion is compared to the last driver
WITH raceData AS (
    SELECT r.raceId, res.time AS champion_time, res2.time AS incremental_time
    FROM races r
    INNER JOIN results res ON r.raceId = res.raceId
    INNER JOIN results res2 ON r.raceId = res2.raceId
    WHERE r.year = 2008 AND r.name = 'Australian Grand Prix' AND res.position = 1
    ORDER BY res2.time DESC
    LIMIT 1
),
timeComponents AS (
    SELECT 
        CAST(SUBSTR(champion_time, 1, 2) AS INTEGER) * 3600000 + -- Hours to milliseconds
        CAST(SUBSTR(champion_time, 4, 2) AS INTEGER) * 60000 + -- Minutes to milliseconds
        CAST(SUBSTR(champion_time, 7, 2) AS INTEGER) * 1000 + -- Seconds to milliseconds
        CAST(SUBSTR(champion_time, 10, 3) AS INTEGER) AS champion_ms,
        CAST(SUBSTR(incremental_time, 1, 2) AS INTEGER) * 3600000 + -- Hours to milliseconds
        CAST(SUBSTR(incremental_time, 4, 2) AS INTEGER) * 60000 + -- Minutes to milliseconds
        CAST(SUBSTR(incremental_time, 7, 2) AS INTEGER) * 1000 + -- Seconds to milliseconds
        CAST(SUBSTR(incremental_time, 10, 3) AS INTEGER) AS incremental_ms
    FROM raceData
)
SELECT 
    ((champion_ms - incremental_ms) * 100.0) / (champion_ms + incremental_ms) AS how_much_faster
FROM timeComponents;

-- SQL query to find the top 3 youngest drivers and count Dutch drivers among them
WITH youngest_drivers AS (
    SELECT code
    FROM drivers
    ORDER BY dob DESC
    LIMIT 3
)
SELECT 
    (SELECT COUNT(*) FROM youngest_drivers WHERE code = 'NL') AS num_dutch_drivers,
    (SELECT GROUP_CONCAT(code, ', ') FROM youngest_drivers) AS top_3_country_codes;

    SELECT code, nationality, dob
    FROM drivers

    LIMIT 3

SELECT 
    (SELECT GROUP_CONCAT(code, ', ') 
     FROM drivers 
     ORDER BY dob DESC 
     LIMIT 3) AS top_3_codes,
    (SELECT COUNT(*)

     WHERE nationality = 'Dutch'

SELECT MIN(p.duration) AS fastest_lap_pit_stop_duration
FROM pitStops AS p
INNER JOIN laptimes AS l ON p.raceId = l.raceId AND p.driverId = l.driverId
INNER JOIN races AS r ON l.raceId = r.raceId
INNER JOIN circuits AS c ON r.circuitId = c.circuitId
WHERE c.name = 'Austrian Grand Prix Circuit'
  AND l.time = (SELECT MIN(l2.time)
                FROM laptimes AS l2
                WHERE l2.raceId = l.raceId);

SELECT ps.duration
FROM pitStops AS ps
INNER JOIN results AS r ON ps.raceId = r.raceId AND ps.driverId = r.driverId
INNER JOIN races AS ra ON r.raceId = ra.raceId
INNER JOIN circuits AS c ON ra.circuitId = c.circuitId
WHERE c.name = 'Austrian Grand Prix Circuit'
  AND r.fastestLapTime IS NOT NULL;

SELECT T4.duration
FROM circuits AS T1
INNER JOIN races AS T2 ON T1.circuitId = T2.circuitId
INNER JOIN results AS T3 ON T2.raceId = T3.raceId
INNER JOIN pitStops AS T4 ON T3.driverId = T4.driverId AND T3.raceId = T4.raceId
WHERE T1.name = 'Austrian Grand Prix Circuit'
  AND T3.fastestLapTime IS NOT NULL;

SELECT pitStops.duration
FROM pitStops
INNER JOIN races ON pitStops.raceId = races.raceId
INNER JOIN circuits ON races.circuitId = circuits.circuitId
INNER JOIN results ON pitStops.raceId = results.raceId
WHERE circuits.name = 'Austrian Grand Prix Circuit'
  AND results.time = (
      SELECT MIN(results.time)
      FROM results
      INNER JOIN races ON results.raceId = races.raceId
      INNER JOIN circuits ON races.circuitId = circuits.circuitId
      WHERE circuits.name = 'Austrian Grand Prix Circuit'
  );

SELECT p.duration
FROM pitStops p
INNER JOIN lapTimes l ON p.driverId = l.driverId AND p.raceId = l.raceId
INNER JOIN races r ON l.raceId = r.raceId
INNER JOIN circuits c ON r.circuitId = c.circuitId
WHERE c.name = 'Austrian Grand Prix Circuit'
  AND l.time = (SELECT MIN(time) FROM lapTimes WHERE raceId = l.raceId);

SELECT duration
FROM pitStops
WHERE driverId = (
    SELECT driverId
    FROM results
    WHERE raceId = (
        SELECT raceId
        FROM races
        WHERE circuitId = (
            SELECT circuitId
            FROM circuits
            WHERE name = 'Austrian Grand Prix Circuit'
        )
    )

)
AND raceId = (
    SELECT raceId
    FROM races
    WHERE circuitId = (
        SELECT circuitId
        FROM circuits
        WHERE name = 'Austrian Grand Prix Circuit'
    )
);

SELECT pitStops.duration
FROM pitStops
INNER JOIN results ON pitStops.driverId = results.driverId AND pitStops.raceId = results.raceId
INNER JOIN races ON results.raceId = races.raceId
INNER JOIN circuits ON races.circuitId = circuits.circuitId
WHERE circuits.name = 'Austrian Grand Prix Circuit'
  AND results.fastestLap = 1;

SELECT pitStops.duration
FROM pitStops
JOIN lapTimes ON pitStops.raceId = lapTimes.raceId AND pitStops.driverId = lapTimes.driverId
JOIN races ON lapTimes.raceId = races.raceId
JOIN circuits ON races.circuitId = circuits.circuitId
WHERE circuits.name = 'Austrian Grand Prix Circuit'
  AND lapTimes.time = (
      SELECT MIN(lapTimes.time)
      FROM lapTimes
      JOIN races ON lapTimes.raceId = races.raceId
      JOIN circuits ON races.circuitId = circuits.circuitId
      WHERE circuits.name = 'Austrian Grand Prix Circuit'
  );

SELECT 
    CAST(SUM(CASE WHEN P.player_name = 'Abdou Diallo' THEN PA.ball_control ELSE 0 END) AS REAL) / 
    SUM(CASE WHEN P.player_name = 'Abdou Diallo' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) - 
    CAST(SUM(CASE WHEN P.player_name = 'Aaron Appindangoye' THEN PA.ball_control ELSE 0 END) AS REAL) / 
    SUM(CASE WHEN P.player_name = 'Aaron Appindangoye' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS diff
FROM 
    Player AS P
INNER JOIN 
    Player_Attributes AS PA
ON 
    P.player_api_id = PA.player_api_id
WHERE 
    P.player_name IN ('Abdou Diallo', 'Aaron Appindangoye');

SELECT MIN(T2.date) AS earliest_date
FROM Player AS T1
INNER JOIN Player_Attributes AS T2
ON T1.player_api_id = T2.player_api_id
WHERE T1.player_name = 'Kevin Constant'
  AND T2.crossing = (
    SELECT MAX(crossing)
    FROM Player_Attributes AS T3
    INNER JOIN Player AS T4
    ON T3.player_api_id = T4.player_api_id
    WHERE T4.player_name = 'Kevin Constant'
  );

SELECT T1.date
FROM Player_Attributes AS T1
INNER JOIN Player AS T2 ON T1.player_api_id = T2.player_api_id
WHERE T2.player_name = 'Kevin Constant'
  AND T1.crossing = (
    SELECT MAX(crossing)
    FROM Player_Attributes AS T3
    INNER JOIN Player AS T4 ON T3.player_api_id = T4.player_api_id
    WHERE T4.player_name = 'Kevin Constant'
  )
ORDER BY T1.date ASC
LIMIT 1;

SELECT MIN(T2.date) AS first_date
FROM Player AS T1
INNER JOIN Player_Attributes AS T2
ON T1.player_api_id = T2.player_api_id
WHERE T1.player_name = 'Kevin Constant'
  AND T2.crossing = (
    SELECT MAX(crossing)
    FROM Player_Attributes AS T3
    INNER JOIN Player AS T4
    ON T3.player_api_id = T4.player_api_id
    WHERE T4.player_name = 'Kevin Constant'
  );

SELECT MIN(PA.date) AS first_highest_crossing_date
FROM Player AS P
INNER JOIN Player_Attributes AS PA
ON P.player_api_id = PA.player_api_id
WHERE P.player_name = 'Kevin Constant'
  AND PA.crossing = (
    SELECT MAX(crossing)
    FROM Player_Attributes AS PA2
    INNER JOIN Player AS P2
    ON PA2.player_api_id = P2.player_api_id
    WHERE P2.player_name = 'Kevin Constant'
  );

SELECT T2.date
FROM Player AS T1
INNER JOIN Player_Attributes AS T2
ON T1.player_api_id = T2.player_api_id
WHERE T1.player_name = 'Kevin Constant'
ORDER BY T2.crossing DESC, T2.date ASC
LIMIT 1;

SELECT MIN(T2.date) AS first_highest_crossing_date
FROM Player AS T1
INNER JOIN Player_Attributes AS T2
ON T1.player_api_id = T2.player_api_id
WHERE T1.player_name = 'Kevin Constant'
AND T2.crossing = (
    SELECT MAX(crossing)

);

        (SUM(CASE WHEN P.player_name = 'Landon Donovan' THEN PA.overall_rating ELSE 0 END) - 
         SUM(CASE WHEN P.player_name = 'Jordan Bowery' THEN PA.overall_rating ELSE 0 END)
        ) AS REAL
    ) * 100.0 /

INNER JOIN

         SUM(CASE WHEN P.player_name = 'Jordan Bowery' THEN PA.overall_rating ELSE 0 END) AS REAL) * 100.0 /

SELECT AVG(height) AS avg_height
FROM (
    SELECT P.height
    FROM Player AS P
    INNER JOIN Match AS M
        ON P.player_api_id = M.home_player_1 OR P.player_api_id = M.home_player_2 OR P.player_api_id = M.home_player_3
        OR P.player_api_id = M.home_player_4 OR P.player_api_id = M.home_player_5 OR P.player_api_id = M.home_player_6
        OR P.player_api_id = M.home_player_7 OR P.player_api_id = M.home_player_8 OR P.player_api_id = M.home_player_9
        OR P.player_api_id = M.home_player_10 OR P.player_api_id = M.home_player_11
    INNER JOIN Team AS T ON M.home_team_api_id = T.team_api_id
    INNER JOIN League AS L ON T.team_api_id = L.country_id
    INNER JOIN Country AS C ON L.country_id = C.id
    WHERE C.name = 'Italy'
    
    UNION ALL
    
    SELECT P.height
    FROM Player AS P
    INNER JOIN Match AS M
        ON P.player_api_id = M.away_player_1 OR P.player_api_id = M.away_player_2 OR P.player_api_id = M.away_player_3
        OR P.player_api_id = M.away_player_4 OR P.player_api_id = M.away_player_5 OR P.player_api_id = M.away_player_6

        OR P.player_api_id = M.away_player_10 OR P.player_api_id = M.away_player_11
    INNER JOIN Team AS T ON M.away_team_api_id = T.team_api_id
    INNER JOIN League AS L ON T.team_api_id = L.country_id
    INNER JOIN Country AS C ON L.country_id = C.id
    WHERE C.name = 'Italy'

SELECT 
    (SUM(CASE WHEN stamina > 80 AND strength > 80 THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) * 100.0) / COUNT(*) AS percentage
FROM 
    Player_Attributes;

WITH filtered_players AS (
    SELECT COUNT(*) AS count_meeting_condition
    FROM Player_Attributes
    WHERE strength > 80 AND stamina > 80
),
total_players AS (
    SELECT COUNT(*) AS total_count
    FROM Player_Attributes
)
SELECT CAST((fp.count_meeting_condition * 100.0) / tp.total_count AS REAL) AS percentage
FROM filtered_players fp, total_players tp;

SELECT 
    (CAST(COUNT(DISTINCT P.id) AS REAL) / (SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT player_api_id) FROM Player_Attributes)) * 100 AS percentage
FROM 
    Player AS P
INNER JOIN 
    Player_Attributes AS PA
ON 
    P.player_api_id = PA.player_api_id
WHERE 
    PA.stamina > 80 AND PA.strength > 80;
