SELECT 
    (CAST(SUM(CASE WHEN Admission = '+' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS REAL) * 100 / COUNT(*)) AS InPatientPercentage,
    (CAST(SUM(CASE WHEN Admission = '-' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS REAL) * 100 / COUNT(*)) AS OutPatientPercentage,
    ABS((CAST(SUM(CASE WHEN Admission = '+' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS REAL) * 100 / COUNT(*)) - 
        (CAST(SUM(CASE WHEN Admission = '-' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS REAL) * 100 / COUNT(*))) AS PercentageDeviation
FROM Patient
WHERE SEX = 'M';

SELECT 
    (CAST(SUM(CASE WHEN Admission = '+' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS REAL) * 100.0 / COUNT(*)) AS inpatient_percentage,
    (CAST(SUM(CASE WHEN Admission = '-' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS REAL) * 100.0 / COUNT(*)) AS outpatient_percentage,
    (CAST(SUM(CASE WHEN Admission = '+' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS REAL) * 100.0 / COUNT(*)) - 
    (CAST(SUM(CASE WHEN Admission = '-' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS REAL) * 100.0 / COUNT(*)) AS percentage_difference
FROM Patient
WHERE SEX = 'M';

-- SQL query to determine if there are more in-patients or out-patients who are male
SELECT 
    CASE 
        WHEN SUM(CASE WHEN SEX = 'M' AND Admission = '+' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) > 
             SUM(CASE WHEN SEX = 'M' AND Admission = '-' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) 
        THEN 'In-patients are more prevalent'
        ELSE 'Out-patients are more prevalent'
    END AS Prevalence,
    (SUM(CASE WHEN SEX = 'M' AND Admission = '+' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) - 
     SUM(CASE WHEN SEX = 'M' AND Admission = '-' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END)) * 100.0 /
    NULLIF(SUM(CASE WHEN SEX = 'M' AND Admission = '-' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END), 0) AS Percentage_Deviation
FROM Patient;

SELECT 
    (CAST(SUM(CASE WHEN Admission = '+' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS REAL) * 100.0) / 
    NULLIF(SUM(CASE WHEN Admission = '-' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END), 0) AS percentage
FROM Patient
WHERE SEX = 'M';

-- SQL query to calculate the required percentages and deviation
SELECT 
    (CAST(COUNT(CASE WHEN SEX = 'M' AND Admission = '+' THEN ID ELSE NULL END) AS REAL) / 
     COUNT(CASE WHEN Admission = '+' THEN ID ELSE NULL END) * 100) AS Male_Inpatient_Percentage,
    
    (CAST(COUNT(CASE WHEN SEX = 'M' AND Admission = '-' THEN ID ELSE NULL END) AS REAL) / 
     COUNT(CASE WHEN Admission = '-' THEN ID ELSE NULL END) * 100) AS Male_Outpatient_Percentage,
    
    ((CAST(COUNT(CASE WHEN SEX = 'M' AND Admission = '+' THEN ID ELSE NULL END) AS REAL) / 
      COUNT(CASE WHEN Admission = '+' THEN ID ELSE NULL END) * 100) -
     (CAST(COUNT(CASE WHEN SEX = 'M' AND Admission = '-' THEN ID ELSE NULL END) AS REAL) / 
      COUNT(CASE WHEN Admission = '-' THEN ID ELSE NULL END) * 100)) AS Percentage_Deviation
FROM Patient;

SELECT 
    CAST(SUM(CASE WHEN Admission = '+' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS REAL) * 100.0 / 
    (SUM(CASE WHEN Admission = '+' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) + SUM(CASE WHEN Admission = '-' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END)) AS Percent_In_Patients,
    CAST(SUM(CASE WHEN Admission = '-' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS REAL) * 100.0 / 
    (SUM(CASE WHEN Admission = '+' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) + SUM(CASE WHEN Admission = '-' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END)) AS Percent_Out_Patients,
    (CAST(SUM(CASE WHEN Admission = '+' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS REAL) * 100.0 / 
    (SUM(CASE WHEN Admission = '+' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) + SUM(CASE WHEN Admission = '-' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END))) - 
    (CAST(SUM(CASE WHEN Admission = '-' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS REAL) * 100.0 / 
    (SUM(CASE WHEN Admission = '+' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) + SUM(CASE WHEN Admission = '-' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END))) AS Deviation
FROM Patient
WHERE SEX = 'M';

SELECT 
    SUM(CASE WHEN Admission = '+' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS Inpatient_Count,
    SUM(CASE WHEN Admission = '-' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS Outpatient_Count,
    CAST(SUM(CASE WHEN Admission = '+' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS REAL) * 100.0 / COUNT(*) AS Inpatient_Percentage,
    CAST(SUM(CASE WHEN Admission = '-' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS REAL) * 100.0 / COUNT(*) AS Outpatient_Percentage,
    CASE 
        WHEN SUM(CASE WHEN Admission = '+' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) > SUM(CASE WHEN Admission = '-' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) THEN 'Inpatient'
        ELSE 'Outpatient'
    END AS Higher_Group
FROM Patient
WHERE SEX = 'M';

SELECT 
    SUM(CASE WHEN Admission = '+' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS Inpatient_Count,
    SUM(CASE WHEN Admission = '-' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS Outpatient_Count,
    CAST(SUM(CASE WHEN Admission = '+' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS REAL) * 100.0 / COUNT(*) AS Inpatient_Percentage,
    CAST(SUM(CASE WHEN Admission = '-' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS REAL) * 100.0 / COUNT(*) AS Outpatient_Percentage,
    CASE 
        WHEN SUM(CASE WHEN Admission = '+' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) > SUM(CASE WHEN Admission = '-' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) THEN 
            (CAST(SUM(CASE WHEN Admission = '+' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS REAL) - CAST(SUM(CASE WHEN Admission = '-' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS REAL)) * 100.0 / COUNT(*)
        ELSE 
            (CAST(SUM(CASE WHEN Admission = '-' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS REAL) - CAST(SUM(CASE WHEN Admission = '+' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS REAL)) * 100.0 / COUNT(*)
    END AS Percentage_Difference
FROM Patient
WHERE SEX = 'M';

SELECT AVG(L.UA) AS AverageUA
FROM Patient P
INNER JOIN Laboratory L ON P.ID = L.ID
WHERE L.Date = (
    SELECT MAX(L2.Date)
    FROM Laboratory L2
    WHERE L2.ID = P.ID
)
AND (
    (P.SEX = 'M' AND L.UA < 8.0)
    OR (P.SEX = 'F' AND L.UA < 6.5)
);

SELECT AVG(L.UA) AS AverageUA
FROM Patient P
INNER JOIN (
    SELECT ID, MAX(`Date`) AS LatestDate
    FROM Laboratory
    GROUP BY ID
) LatestLab ON P.ID = LatestLab.ID
INNER JOIN Laboratory L ON LatestLab.ID = L.ID AND LatestLab.LatestDate = L.`Date`
WHERE (P.SEX = 'M' AND L.UA < 8.0) OR (P.SEX = 'F' AND L.UA < 6.5);

-- SQL query to calculate the average UA index for patients with normal UA based on their latest lab result
WITH LatestLabResults AS (
    SELECT L.ID, L.UA, P.SEX,
           ROW_NUMBER() OVER (PARTITION BY L.ID ORDER BY L.Date DESC) AS rn
    FROM Laboratory L
    INNER JOIN Patient P ON L.ID = P.ID
)
SELECT AVG(UA) AS AverageUA
FROM LatestLabResults
WHERE rn = 1 AND
      ((SEX = 'M' AND UA < 8.0) OR (SEX = 'F' AND UA < 6.5));

    SELECT
        L.ID,
        L.UA,
        ROW_NUMBER() OVER (PARTITION BY L.ID ORDER BY L.Date DESC) AS rn
    FROM Laboratory L
)

                INNER JOIN event AS e2 ON b2.link_to_event = e2.event_id

-- SQL query to find cities and states for events with total income > 40
SELECT DISTINCT z.city, z.state
FROM income i
INNER JOIN budget b ON i.link_to_member = b.budget_id
INNER JOIN event e ON b.link_to_event = e.event_id
INNER JOIN zip_code z ON e.location = z.zip_code
GROUP BY e.event_id
HAVING SUM(i.amount) > 40;

    z.city, 
    z.county
FROM 
    income i
INNER JOIN 
    member m ON i.link_to_member = m.member_id
INNER JOIN 
    zip_code z ON m.zip = z.zip_code
GROUP BY 
    z.city, z.county
HAVING 
    SUM(i.amount) > 40;

1481:
WITH CustomerConsumption AS (
    -- Step 1: Calculate total consumption for each customer in each segment
    SELECT
        c.Segment,
        c.CustomerID,
        SUM(y.Consumption) AS TotalConsumption
    FROM customers c
    INNER JOIN yearmonth y ON c.CustomerID = y.CustomerID
    WHERE c.Currency = 'CZK' AND y.Date BETWEEN '201301' AND '201312'
    GROUP BY c.Segment, c.CustomerID
),
LowestConsumption AS (
    -- Step 2: Find the lowest total consumption for each segment
    SELECT
        Segment,
        MIN(TotalConsumption) AS MinConsumption
    FROM CustomerConsumption
    GROUP BY Segment
),
SegmentCustomers AS (
    -- Step 3: Identify customers with the lowest consumption in each segment
    SELECT
        cc.Segment,
        cc.CustomerID
    FROM CustomerConsumption cc
    INNER JOIN LowestConsumption lc
        ON cc.Segment = lc.Segment AND cc.TotalConsumption = lc.MinConsumption
),
TotalSegmentConsumption AS (
    -- Step 4: Calculate total consumption for these customers in each segment
    SELECT
        s.Segment,
        SUM(y.Consumption) AS TotalSegmentConsumption
    FROM SegmentCustomers s
    INNER JOIN yearmonth y ON s.CustomerID = y.CustomerID
    WHERE y.Date BETWEEN '201301' AND '201312'
    GROUP BY s.Segment
),
SegmentCount AS (
    -- Step 5: Count the number of customers with the lowest consumption in each segment
    SELECT
        s.Segment,
        COUNT(s.CustomerID) AS CustomerCount
    FROM SegmentCustomers s
    GROUP BY s.Segment
),
AnnualAverage AS (
    -- Step 6: Calculate the annual average consumption for each segment
    SELECT
        tsc.Segment,
        tsc.TotalSegmentConsumption / sc.CustomerCount AS AnnualAverage
    FROM TotalSegmentConsumption tsc
    INNER JOIN SegmentCount sc ON tsc.Segment = sc.Segment
)
-- Step 7: Calculate the required differences
SELECT
    (SELECT AnnualAverage FROM AnnualAverage WHERE Segment = 'SME') - 
    (SELECT AnnualAverage FROM AnnualAverage WHERE Segment = 'LAM') AS DiffSMEvsLAM,
    (SELECT AnnualAverage FROM AnnualAverage WHERE Segment = 'LAM') - 
    (SELECT AnnualAverage FROM AnnualAverage WHERE Segment = 'KAM') AS DiffLAMvsKAM,
    (SELECT AnnualAverage FROM AnnualAverage WHERE Segment = 'KAM') - 
    (SELECT AnnualAverage FROM AnnualAverage WHERE Segment = 'SME') AS DiffKAMvsSME;

WITH LowConsumptionCTE AS (

    FROM customers c
    INNER JOIN yearmonth ym ON c.CustomerID = ym.CustomerID
    WHERE c.Currency = 'CZK'
      AND ym.Date BETWEEN '201301' AND '201312'
      AND ym.Consumption = (
          SELECT MIN(ym2.Consumption)
          FROM yearmonth ym2
          INNER JOIN customers c2 ON ym2.CustomerID = c2.CustomerID
          WHERE c2.Segment = c.Segment
            AND c2.Currency = 'CZK'
            AND ym2.Date BETWEEN '201301' AND '201312'
      )
),
AnnualAverageCTE AS (
    SELECT Segment,
           SUM(Consumption) AS TotalConsumption,
           COUNT(CustomerID) AS CustomerCount
    FROM LowConsumptionCTE
    GROUP BY Segment
)
SELECT 
    (SELECT TotalConsumption / CustomerCount FROM AnnualAverageCTE WHERE Segment = 'SME') -
    (SELECT TotalConsumption / CustomerCount FROM AnnualAverageCTE WHERE Segment = 'LAM') AS SMEvsLAM,
    (SELECT TotalConsumption / CustomerCount FROM AnnualAverageCTE WHERE Segment = 'LAM') -

    (SELECT TotalConsumption / CustomerCount FROM AnnualAverageCTE WHERE Segment = 'KAM') -

-- SQL query to calculate the required differences in annual average consumption
WITH CustomerConsumption AS (
    SELECT
        c.Segment,
        y.CustomerID,
        MIN(y.Consumption) AS MinConsumption
    FROM yearmonth y
    INNER JOIN customers c ON y.CustomerID = c.CustomerID
    WHERE c.Currency = 'CZK' AND y.Date BETWEEN '201301' AND '201312'
    GROUP BY c.Segment, y.CustomerID
),
SegmentTotals AS (
    SELECT
        c.Segment,
        SUM(y.Consumption) AS TotalConsumption,
        COUNT(c.CustomerID) AS CustomerCount
    FROM yearmonth y
    INNER JOIN customers c ON y.CustomerID = c.CustomerID
    WHERE c.Currency = 'CZK' AND y.Date BETWEEN '201301' AND '201312'
    GROUP BY c.Segment
),
AnnualAverages AS (
    SELECT
        s.Segment,
        s.TotalConsumption / s.CustomerCount AS AnnualAverage
    FROM SegmentTotals s
)
SELECT
    (SELECT AnnualAverage FROM AnnualAverages WHERE Segment = 'SME') -
    (SELECT AnnualAverage FROM AnnualAverages WHERE Segment = 'LAM') AS DiffSMEvsLAM,
    (SELECT AnnualAverage FROM AnnualAverages WHERE Segment = 'LAM') -
    (SELECT AnnualAverage FROM AnnualAverages WHERE Segment = 'KAM') AS DiffLAMvsKAM,
    (SELECT AnnualAverage FROM AnnualAverages WHERE Segment = 'KAM') -
    (SELECT AnnualAverage FROM AnnualAverages WHERE Segment = 'SME') AS DiffKAMvsSME;

-- SQL query to calculate the differences in annual average consumption
WITH LowestConsumption AS (

    FROM yearmonth y
    INNER JOIN customers c ON y.CustomerID = c.CustomerID
    WHERE y.Date LIKE '2013%' AND c.Currency = 'CZK'
    GROUP BY c.Segment
),
SegmentConsumption AS (
    SELECT c.Segment, SUM(y.Consumption) AS TotalConsumption, COUNT(DISTINCT y.CustomerID) AS CustomerCount
    FROM yearmonth y
    INNER JOIN customers c ON y.CustomerID = c.CustomerID
    WHERE y.Date LIKE '2013%' AND c.Currency = 'CZK'
    AND c.Segment IN (SELECT Segment FROM LowestConsumption)
    GROUP BY c.Segment
),
AnnualAverage AS (
    SELECT Segment, TotalConsumption / CustomerCount AS AnnualAverage
    FROM SegmentConsumption
)
SELECT
    (SELECT AnnualAverage FROM AnnualAverage WHERE Segment = 'SME') - (SELECT AnnualAverage FROM AnnualAverage WHERE Segment = 'LAM') AS SMEvsLAM,
    (SELECT AnnualAverage FROM AnnualAverage WHERE Segment = 'LAM') - (SELECT AnnualAverage FROM AnnualAverage WHERE Segment = 'KAM') AS LAMvsKAM,
    (SELECT AnnualAverage FROM AnnualAverage WHERE Segment = 'KAM') - (SELECT AnnualAverage FROM AnnualAverage WHERE Segment = 'SME') AS KAMvsSME;

-- SQL query to calculate the differences in annual average consumption
WITH LowestConsumption AS (
    SELECT
        c.Segment,
        MIN(y.Consumption) AS MinConsumption
    FROM customers c
    INNER JOIN yearmonth y ON c.CustomerID = y.CustomerID
    WHERE c.Currency = 'CZK' AND y.Date LIKE '2013%'
    GROUP BY c.Segment
),
SegmentConsumption AS (
    SELECT
        c.Segment,
        SUM(y.Consumption) AS TotalConsumption,
        COUNT(DISTINCT c.CustomerID) AS CustomerCount
    FROM customers c
    INNER JOIN yearmonth y ON c.CustomerID = y.CustomerID

    WHERE c.Currency = 'CZK' AND y.Date LIKE '2013%'
    GROUP BY c.Segment
)
SELECT
    (SELECT TotalConsumption / CustomerCount FROM SegmentConsumption WHERE Segment = 'SME') -

    (SELECT TotalConsumption / CustomerCount FROM SegmentConsumption WHERE Segment = 'LAM') -
    (SELECT TotalConsumption / CustomerCount FROM SegmentConsumption WHERE Segment = 'KAM') AS Difference_LAM_KAM,
    (SELECT TotalConsumption / CustomerCount FROM SegmentConsumption WHERE Segment = 'KAM') -
    (SELECT TotalConsumption / CustomerCount FROM SegmentConsumption WHERE Segment = 'SME') AS Difference_KAM_SME;

WITH CustomerConsumption AS (

        c.Segment,
        y.CustomerID,
        MIN(y.Consumption) AS LowestConsumption
    FROM customers c
    JOIN yearmonth y ON c.CustomerID = y.CustomerID
    WHERE c.Currency = 'CZK' AND y.Date BETWEEN '201301' AND '201312'
    GROUP BY c.Segment
),
LowestConsumers AS (
    SELECT
        c.Segment,
        c.CustomerID
    FROM CustomerConsumption cc
    JOIN customers c ON cc.CustomerID = c.CustomerID
    WHERE c.Currency = 'CZK' AND cc.LowestConsumption = (
        SELECT MIN(LowestConsumption) AS MinConsumption
        FROM CustomerConsumption
        WHERE Segment = c.Segment
    )
),
TotalConsumption AS (
    SELECT
        c.Segment,
        SUM(y.Consumption) AS TotalConsumption
    FROM LowestConsumers lc
    JOIN customers c ON lc.CustomerID = c.CustomerID
    JOIN yearmonth y ON lc.CustomerID = y.CustomerID
    WHERE c.Currency = 'CZK' AND y.Date BETWEEN '201301' AND '201312'
    GROUP BY c.Segment
),
AnnualAverage AS (
    SELECT
        tc.Segment,
        tc.TotalConsumption / COUNT(lc.CustomerID) AS AnnualAverage
    FROM TotalConsumption tc
    JOIN LowestConsumers lc ON tc.Segment = lc.Segment
    GROUP BY tc.Segment
)
SELECT
    (SELECT AnnualAverage FROM AnnualAverage WHERE Segment = 'SME') - (SELECT AnnualAverage FROM AnnualAverage WHERE Segment = 'LAM') AS SMEvsLAM,
    (SELECT AnnualAverage FROM AnnualAverage WHERE Segment = 'LAM') - (SELECT AnnualAverage FROM AnnualAverage WHERE Segment = 'KAM') AS LAMvsKAM,
    (SELECT AnnualAverage FROM AnnualAverage WHERE Segment = 'KAM') - (SELECT AnnualAverage FROM AnnualAverage WHERE Segment = 'SME') AS KAMvsSME;

SELECT
    -- Difference in annual average between SME and LAM
    (SELECT SUM(y.Consumption) / COUNT(DISTINCT y.CustomerID)

     INNER JOIN customers AS c ON y.CustomerID = c.CustomerID
     WHERE c.Segment = 'SME' AND c.Currency = 'CZK' AND y.Date BETWEEN '201301' AND '201312'
    ) - (SELECT SUM(y.Consumption) / COUNT(DISTINCT y.CustomerID)
         FROM yearmonth AS y
         INNER JOIN customers AS c ON y.CustomerID = c.CustomerID
         WHERE c.Segment = 'LAM' AND c.Currency = 'CZK' AND y.Date BETWEEN '201301' AND '201312'
        ) AS Difference_SME_LAM,

    -- Difference in annual average between LAM and KAM
    (SELECT SUM(y.Consumption) / COUNT(DISTINCT y.CustomerID)
     FROM yearmonth AS y
     INNER JOIN customers AS c ON y.CustomerID = c.CustomerID
     WHERE c.Segment = 'LAM' AND c.Currency = 'CZK' AND y.Date BETWEEN '201301' AND '201312'
    ) - (SELECT SUM(y.Consumption) / COUNT(DISTINCT y.CustomerID)
         FROM yearmonth AS y
         INNER JOIN customers AS c ON y.CustomerID = c.CustomerID
         WHERE c.Segment = 'KAM' AND c.Currency = 'CZK' AND y.Date BETWEEN '201301' AND '201312'
        ) AS Difference_LAM_KAM,

    -- Difference in annual average between KAM and SME
    (SELECT SUM(y.Consumption) / COUNT(DISTINCT y.CustomerID)
     FROM yearmonth AS y
     INNER JOIN customers AS c ON y.CustomerID = c.CustomerID
     WHERE c.Segment = 'KAM' AND c.Currency = 'CZK' AND y.Date BETWEEN '201301' AND '201312'
    ) - (SELECT SUM(y.Consumption) / COUNT(DISTINCT y.CustomerID)
         FROM yearmonth AS y
         INNER JOIN customers AS c ON y.CustomerID = c.CustomerID
         WHERE c.Segment = 'SME' AND c.Currency = 'CZK' AND y.Date BETWEEN '201301' AND '201312'
        ) AS Difference_KAM_SME;

WITH LowestConsumption AS (
    SELECT
        c.Segment,
        SUM(y.Consumption) AS TotalConsumption,
        COUNT(*) AS CustomerCount
    FROM
        customers c
    INNER JOIN

    ON

),
AnnualAverage AS (

SELECT

-- SQL query to find the segments with the biggest and smallest percentage increases in consumption
WITH Consumption AS (
    SELECT
        c.Segment,
        ym.CustomerID,
        SUM(CASE WHEN SUBSTR(ym.Date, 1, 4) = '2013' THEN ym.Consumption ELSE 0 END) AS Consumption2013,
        SUM(CASE WHEN SUBSTR(ym.Date, 1, 4) = '2012' THEN ym.Consumption ELSE 0 END) AS Consumption2012
    FROM customers c
    JOIN yearmonth ym ON c.CustomerID = ym.CustomerID
    WHERE c.Currency = 'EUR' AND c.Segment IN ('SME', 'LAM', 'KAM')
    GROUP BY c.Segment, ym.CustomerID
),
PercentageIncrease AS (
    SELECT
        Segment,
        CustomerID,
        (Consumption2013 - Consumption2012) AS IncreaseDecrease,
        (CASE WHEN Consumption2013 = 0 THEN NULL ELSE (IncreaseDecrease * 100.0 / Consumption2013) END) AS PercentageIncrease
    FROM Consumption
)
SELECT
    Segment,
    MAX(PercentageIncrease) AS MaxPercentageIncrease,
    MIN(PercentageIncrease) AS MinPercentageIncrease
FROM PercentageIncrease
GROUP BY Segment
ORDER BY MAX(PercentageIncrease) DESC, MIN(PercentageIncrease) ASC;

WITH SegmentConsumption AS (
    SELECT
        c.Segment,
        SUM(CASE WHEN SUBSTR(y.Date, 1, 4) = '2013' THEN y.Consumption ELSE 0 END) AS Total2013,
        SUM(CASE WHEN SUBSTR(y.Date, 1, 4) = '2012' THEN y.Consumption ELSE 0 END) AS Total2012
    FROM
        customers c
    INNER JOIN
        yearmonth y
    ON
        c.CustomerID = y.CustomerID
    WHERE
        c.Currency = 'EUR'
        AND c.Segment IN ('SME', 'LAM', 'KAM')
    GROUP BY
        c.Segment
),
SegmentIncrease AS (
    SELECT
        Segment,
        Total2013,
        Total2012,
        (Total2013 - Total2012) AS Increase,
        CASE
            WHEN Total2013 = 0 THEN 0
            ELSE (Total2013 - Total2012) / Total2013 * 100
        END AS PercentageIncrease
    FROM
        SegmentConsumption
)
SELECT
    MAX(PercentageIncrease) AS MaxIncreaseSegment,
    MIN(PercentageIncrease) AS MinIncreaseSegment
FROM
    SegmentIncrease;

WITH SegmentConsumption AS (
    SELECT
        c.Segment,
        SUM(CASE WHEN ym.Date LIKE '2012%' THEN ym.Consumption ELSE 0 END) AS Consumption2012,
        SUM(CASE WHEN ym.Date LIKE '2013%' THEN ym.Consumption ELSE 0 END) AS Consumption2013
    FROM customers c
    INNER JOIN yearmonth ym ON c.CustomerID = ym.CustomerID
    WHERE c.Currency = 'EUR'
    GROUP BY c.Segment
),
PercentageIncrease AS (
    SELECT
        Segment,
        (Consumption2013 - Consumption2012) * 100.0 / Consumption2013 AS PercentIncrease
    FROM SegmentConsumption
    WHERE Consumption2013 > 0
)
SELECT
    MAX(PERCENTINCREASE) AS MaxPercentIncrease,
    MIN(PERCENTINCREASE) AS MinPercentIncrease
FROM PercentageIncrease;

-- SQL query to find the segments with the biggest and smallest percentage increases in consumption
WITH segment_consumption AS (
    SELECT
        c.Segment,
        SUM(CASE WHEN y.Date LIKE '2012%' THEN y.Consumption ELSE 0 END) AS Consumption_2012,
        SUM(CASE WHEN y.Date LIKE '2013%' THEN y.Consumption ELSE 0 END) AS Consumption_2013
    FROM
        customers c
    INNER JOIN
        yearmonth y
    ON
        c.CustomerID = y.CustomerID
    WHERE
        c.Currency = 'EUR' AND c.Segment IN ('SME', 'LAM', 'KAM')
    GROUP BY
        c.Segment
),
percentage_increase AS (
    SELECT
        Segment,
        (Consumption_2013 - Consumption_2012) AS Increase_or_Decrease,
        CASE
            WHEN Consumption_2013 = 0 THEN NULL
            ELSE (Consumption_2013 - Consumption_2012) * 100.0 / Consumption_2013
        END AS Percentage_Increase
    FROM
        segment_consumption
)
SELECT
    MAX(CASE WHEN Percentage_Increase = (SELECT MAX(Percentage_Increase) FROM percentage_increase) THEN Segment END) AS Segment_Max_Increase,
    MAX(CASE WHEN Percentage_Increase = (SELECT MIN(Percentage_Increase) FROM percentage_increase) THEN Segment END) AS Segment_Min_Increase
FROM
    percentage_increase;

WITH SegmentConsumption AS (
    SELECT
        c.Segment,
        SUM(CASE WHEN ym.Date LIKE '2012%' THEN ym.Consumption ELSE 0 END) AS Consumption2012,
        SUM(CASE WHEN ym.Date LIKE '2013%' THEN ym.Consumption ELSE 0 END) AS Consumption2013
    FROM
        customers c
    INNER JOIN
        yearmonth ym
    ON
        c.CustomerID = ym.CustomerID
    WHERE
        c.Segment IN ('SME', 'LAM', 'KAM') AND c.Currency = 'EUR'
    GROUP BY
        c.Segment
),
PercentageIncrease AS (
    SELECT
        Segment,
        (Consumption2013 - Consumption2012) * 100.0 / Consumption2013 AS PercentageChange
    FROM
        SegmentConsumption
    WHERE
        Consumption2013 > 0 -- Avoid division by zero
)
SELECT
    MAX(PercentageChange) AS LargestIncrease,
    MIN(PercentageChange) AS SmallestIncrease
FROM
    PercentageIncrease;

-- SQL query to find the segments with the biggest and lowest percentage increases in consumption
WITH ConsumptionData AS (
    SELECT
        c.Segment,
        SUM(CASE WHEN SUBSTR(y.Date, 1, 4) = '2012' THEN y.Consumption ELSE 0 END) AS Consumption2012,
        SUM(CASE WHEN SUBSTR(y.Date, 1, 4) = '2013' THEN y.Consumption ELSE 0 END) AS Consumption2013
    FROM
        customers c
    INNER JOIN
        yearmonth y
    ON
        c.CustomerID = y.CustomerID
    WHERE
        c.Currency = 'EUR'
        AND c.Segment IN ('SME', 'LAM', 'KAM')
    GROUP BY
        c.Segment
)
SELECT
    Segment,
    (Consumption2013 - Consumption2012) AS IncreaseOrDecrease,
    ((Consumption2013 - Consumption2012) * 100.0 / Consumption2013) AS PercentageChange
FROM
    ConsumptionData
WHERE
    Consumption2013 > 0 -- Ensure no division by zero
ORDER BY
    PercentageChange DESC
LIMIT 1; -- Biggest increase

-- Run the query again with ORDER BY PercentageChange ASC LIMIT 1 to find the lowest increase

-- SQL query to find the segments with the largest and smallest percentage increases in consumption
WITH SegmentConsumption AS (
    SELECT
        c.Segment,
        SUM(CASE WHEN y.Date LIKE '2013%' THEN y.Consumption ELSE 0 END) AS Consumption_2013,
        SUM(CASE WHEN y.Date LIKE '2012%' THEN y.Consumption ELSE 0 END) AS Consumption_2012
    FROM customers c
    INNER JOIN yearmonth y ON c.CustomerID = y.CustomerID
    WHERE c.Currency = 'EUR' AND c.Segment IN ('SME', 'LAM', 'KAM')
    GROUP BY c.Segment
),
PercentageIncrease AS (
    SELECT
        Segment,
        (Consumption_2013 - Consumption_2012) AS Increase,
        (CAST(Consumption_2013 - Consumption_2012 AS REAL) / Consumption_2013) * 100 AS Percentage_Increase
    FROM SegmentConsumption
)
SELECT
    (SELECT Segment FROM PercentageIncrease ORDER BY Percentage_Increase DESC LIMIT 1) AS Largest_Increase_Segment,
    (SELECT Segment FROM PercentageIncrease ORDER BY Percentage_Increase ASC LIMIT 1) AS Smallest_Increase_Segment;

-- SQL query to find the segments with the biggest and smallest percentage increase in consumption (2013 vs. 2012 in EUR)
WITH segment_consumption AS (
    SELECT
        c.Segment,
        SUM(CASE WHEN SUBSTR(y.Date, 1, 4) = '2012' THEN y.Consumption ELSE 0 END) AS consumption_2012,
        SUM(CASE WHEN SUBSTR(y.Date, 1, 4) = '2013' THEN y.Consumption ELSE 0 END) AS consumption_2013
    FROM customers c
    INNER JOIN yearmonth y ON c.CustomerID = y.CustomerID
    WHERE c.Segment IN ('SME', 'LAM', 'KAM') AND c.Currency = 'EUR'
    GROUP BY c.Segment
)
SELECT
    'Biggest Increase' AS type,
    Segment
FROM (
    SELECT
        Segment,
        (consumption_2013 - consumption_2012) * 100.0 / consumption_2013 AS percentage_increase
    FROM segment_consumption
    WHERE consumption_2013 > 0
    ORDER BY percentage_increase DESC
    LIMIT 1
)
UNION ALL
SELECT
    'Smallest Increase' AS type,
    Segment
FROM (
    SELECT
        Segment,
        (consumption_2013 - consumption_2012) * 100.0 / consumption_2013 AS percentage_increase
    FROM segment_consumption
    WHERE consumption_2013 > 0
    ORDER BY percentage_increase ASC
    LIMIT 1
);

-- SQL query to find the top spending customer and their average price per item
WITH CustomerSpending AS (
    SELECT
        T.CustomerID,
        SUM(T.Amount) AS TotalSpending,
        SUM(T.Price) AS TotalPrice
    FROM
        transactions_1k AS T
    GROUP BY
        T.CustomerID
),
TopSpendingCustomer AS (
    SELECT
        CustomerID,
        TotalSpending,
        TotalPrice
    FROM
        CustomerSpending
    ORDER BY
        TotalSpending DESC
    LIMIT 1
)
SELECT
    TSC.CustomerID,
    TSC.TotalSpending / TSC.TotalPrice AS AvgPricePerItem,
    C.Currency
FROM
    TopSpendingCustomer AS TSC
INNER JOIN
    customers AS C
ON
    TSC.CustomerID = C.CustomerID;
